{"hypothesis_id": "HD1", "rev": 31, "ts": "2026-05-18T11:25:00Z", "statement": "DESIGN-LOCK REFINEMENT to rev29 (user-decided 2026-05-18 from the rev30 learning curve; NO compute spent; rev28/rev30 'refuted' verdict UNCHANGED). The rev30 curve (LTC-H180) shows the val-optimum at epoch ~3 (val_ric +0.0355@ep3, test_ric +0.0111@ep3, near the +0.0131@ep2 OOS peak) and clear overfit by ep5-8; the frozen rev25 rule (patience=5 on R1-val-logloss, cosine T_max=30) fires at ep8 -- already past the optimum, val_ll 0.69->0.73, test_ric negative. So for ALL FUTURE TCN-arch studies the rev29 early-stop spec is tightened: (1) patience 5 -> 2 (small; stop shortly after the val-skill optimum, not deep into overfit) -- combined with the rev29-locked select-on-VAL-SKILL (val rank_ic/AUC, NOT logloss) AND mandatory restore-best-checkpoint + min-delta on the val-skill metric (so a 1-epoch noise dip cannot end the run prematurely and the RESTORED weights are the val-skill argmax, not the last epoch); (2) cosine LR T_max shrunk 30 -> ~12 (matched to the realized short stop; a 30-epoch schedule is mis-sized when the model is done by ~ep3 -- the LR never anneals near the actual stop); (3) keep a generous absolute epoch CAP (e.g. 40) purely as a safety ceiling, never the expected stop. CAVEAT (honest, pre-registered): patience=2 / T_max~12 are calibrated on ONE cell (LTC-H180, seed0); the curve shape is program-consistent (weak ~0.51 signal -> rapid overfit-on-noise at ~16k train rows) but the FIRST future TCN-arch grid run MUST treat its own per-(sym,H,seed) curves as the calibration set and re-validate these constants before they are trusted as fixed -- do NOT hard-freeze a schedule off n=1. Net rev29 locks now read: D=4 fixed; 3-seed error-bar {0,1,2}; per-(sym,H) L prior; select+early-stop on val-skill with patience=2, restore-best, min-delta, cosine T_max~12, abs-cap~40; primary lever for any rescue attempt remains capacity/regularization/data (rev30), NOT epochs. HD1-seq stays refuted/shelved; pivot user-owned.", "status": "refuted", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": "lcurve-20260518-104527", "note": "rev29 lock refined off rev30 curve: patience 5->2, cosine T_max 30->~12, restore-best+min-delta on val-skill, abs-cap~40. Saves compute/time AND avoids the overfit region (val-opt ~ep3). Explicit n=1-calibration caveat: first future grid run re-validates these constants. No compute spent; rev28/rev30 verdict unchanged; HD1-seq refuted/shelved; pivot user-owned."}
