{"hypothesis_id": "HD1", "rev": 42, "ts": "2026-05-18T17:05:00Z", "statement": "SCOPE TIGHTENING of the Tier-0 'capacity/reg INERT' verdict (rev39/rev41) -- prompted by a valid reviewer challenge that 'ignore those configs' was over-generalized. NO rerun, NO science/data change; rev32 (frozen spec), rev35 (design-lock framing), rev28 (refuted-shelved), rev39/rev41 (Tier-0 result + rev4 perf) ALL UNCHANGED; experiments.jsonl untouched. CLARIFICATION OF WHAT TIER-0 PROVED (narrow): under the frozen rev32 spec (D=4 TCN, BCE objective, last-step head, fixed schedule, the 4 cells, ~16k samples/cell, fixed split) the W/dropout/wd axis does not move the MARGINAL SINGLE-MODEL rank_IC beyond the ~0.003-0.004 run-to-run noise band on >=3/4 incl weak control, and the per-cell argmax is unstable (rev4 vs rev39 flip = empirical proof of noise). That is a NULL MAIN EFFECT ON ONE METRIC IN ONE REGIME -- and ONLY that. WHAT TIER-0 DID NOT PROVE (the verdict must NOT be cited for these): (1) ENSEMBLE diversity -- selection metric was marginal mean rank_IC; ensemble value depends on the covariance of prediction residuals, not marginal skill; two configs with statistically indistinguishable mean rank_IC can have residual correlation well below 1 (different capacity/receptive-field captures partially different signal). 'W inert for a single model' does NOT imply 'W irrelevant in an ensemble'; Tier-0 is SILENT on this. (2) INTERACTIONS with Tier-1 axes -- inertness measured at FIXED objective=BCE, head=last-step; says nothing about W x objective or W x head (a pairwise/rank-IC loss or temporal-pooling head can make capacity a live lever; design non-separability). (3) DATA SCALE -- at ~16k samples W=64 may be data-starved; with 5-10x data larger capacity can overtake (capacity-data coupled; double descent). Verdict was explicitly 'INERT in this range' => regime-scoped, NOT universal. REFINED POSITION: lock W=16 is correct ONLY as a SCOPED, REVISABLE DEFAULT for the Tier-1 baseline (null main effect => cheapest+most-regularized default costs nothing in expectation, rev30) -- it is NOT a permanent pruning of those configs. Symmetric anti-self-deception discipline: within a ~0.003 noise band one can ALWAYS find a 'decorrelated' or 'promising-under-interaction' member; therefore any re-opening of the axis must be its OWN pre-registered test (weak-control + OOS-measured decorrelation + noise-floor + seed-sd reported), NOT retro-mined from Tier-0's noisy numbers. MANDATORY RE-OPEN TRIGGERS for W (always swept JOINTLY, never alone): (a) ENSEMBLE on the roadmap -> pre-registered ensemble-IC test: OOS ensemble IC vs best single, decorrelation measured OOS, with weak control; (b) any Tier-1 axis shows a real effect -> confirmatory re-probe of W at the new winning objective/head BEFORE final lock (interaction check); (c) a data-scaling effort -> joint capacity x data sweep (sweeping one with the other fixed is the separability error). NET: the rev39/rev41 design-lock decision STANDS as a scoped default; this rev only prevents the conclusion from being mis-extended to ensemble/interaction/scale regimes it never tested. This sharpens rather than weakens the program's integrity (rev35 winner's-curse discipline, applied symmetrically to both pruning AND resurrection).", "status": "testing", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "note": "Scope fix (reviewer-prompted): Tier-0 proved a NULL MARGINAL single-model rank_IC main effect for W/do/wd in THIS spec+regime ONLY. Does NOT cover (1) ensemble decorrelation, (2) Tier-1-axis interactions, (3) data-scale. W=16 lock = scoped revisable DEFAULT, not permanent pruning. Re-open W (jointly) on: ensemble (own pre-reg ensemble-IC test), real Tier-1 effect (interaction re-probe), data scaling (joint capacity x data). Re-opening must be its own pre-registered weak-control test, not retro-mined from Tier-0 noise. rev32/35/28/39/41 + experiments.jsonl UNCHANGED."}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD1", "rev": 43, "ts": "2026-05-18T17:40:00Z", "statement": "TIER-1 PRE-REGISTRATION (FROZEN spec; recorded BEFORE any run, rev32-style discipline; runner will reuse the rev4 multi-GPU substrate). DECISION (user-confirmed 2026-05-18): Tier 1 probes the TCN objective/head axis -- the remaining 'have we really exhausted TCN' lever before escalating 'TCN ~= snapshot fundamentally' (rev28/rev30/rev39). Ensemble capacity-diversity (rev42 trigger a) is NOT actionable yet (no non-XGBoost members to ensemble) -> deferred. FROZEN DESIGN: 2x2 factorial objective{BCE [=reference], pairwise-logistic} x head{last-step [=reference], mean-pool}, at LOCKED W=16 & D=4 (rev39/rev41 scoped default), frozen rev32 data regime (same 4 cells: BTC-USDT-PERP H180/L512, BTC-USDT-PERP H300/L512, ETH-USDT-PERP H180/L256, LTC-USDT-PERP H300/L128 = WEAK CONTROL; same honest split / r1-weights / standardization / EP_CAP/PATIENCE/T_MAX schedule), SEEDS=(0,1,2). Units = 4 combos x 4 cells x 3 seeds = 48. The (BCE,last-step) corner = the in-run REFERENCE (== rev32/rev25 setting at W16; computed FRESH this run to control the ~0.001-0.003 run-to-run CUDA nondeterminism established in rev41). FROZEN OPERATOR DEFINITIONS: pairwise-logistic = RankNet over all in-batch pairs with sign(rH_i - rH_j) != 0, target = 1{rH_i > rH_j}, ranking key = the CONTINUOUS H-horizon return rH (NOT the binary up/down label), loss = BCE(sigmoid(s_i - s_j), target) averaged over those pairs, s = model scalar score; BCE branch = unchanged from Tier-0 (r1-weighted BCE on up/down). mean-pool head = arithmetic mean over the temporal axis of the TCN feature map before the final linear (vs last-step = current). EVAL METRIC UNCHANGED: rank_IC = auc(up/down) - 0.5 (+ placebo + block-bootstrap SE), identical to Tier-0; objective changes TRAINING only, never eval. PRE-REGISTERED DECISION RULE: for each non-reference combo C and cell, lift(C,cell) = ric_mean(C,cell) - ric_mean(BCE/last-step,cell) with BOTH means from