{"hypothesis_id": "HD1", "rev": 48, "ts": "2026-05-20T19:06:50Z", "statement": "TIER-2 EXPLORATORY PROBE PRE-REG (architecture-on-raw-L2; sub-tier of rev45, weak-control-only; spec recorded BEFORE any build/run; CLAUDE.md rules 1-3 exploratory frame). QUESTION (single, narrow): under the frozen rev45 data regime, at LTC-USDT-PERP H=300 L=512 D=8 (RF-matched), does the OLD TCNClassifier-style architecture -- (a) capacity W=128 (vs the rev44/rev45-locked W=16) AND (b) a two-stream input with raw 20-level LOB temporal stream + last-tick engineered-globals scalar stream (vs the current single-stream 46-engineered-feature input) -- shift LTC-H300 rank_IC vs the rev47 anchor (+0.0240+-0.0069 at L512, W16, D8)? Single ARCHITECTURE-VARIATION cell, single capacity, 3 seeds = 3 units, $1-3 total. PRIMARY DELIVERABLE (per CLAUDE.md rules 1/2 -- the surface, NOT a verdict): rank_IC_mean +- seed_sd for the probe and the rev47 anchor on the SAME cell, reported side-by-side. SECONDARY: per-seed values; placebo_ric; block-bootstrap SE. NO sec5/refuted/confirmed binding; this is descriptive characterization of a single point on a much larger architecture x representation surface. WEAK-CONTROL CAVEAT (recorded): rev47 LTC seed-sd=0.0069 -> any |lift|<~0.014 is within seed-noise on this cell; the probe answers an EXISTENCE question (does anything visible happen) NOT a definitive yes/no on architecture in HD1. L<<H CAVEAT (recorded, measured 2026-05-20): LTC tick rate ~129ms median, ~727ms mean -> L=512 ticks covers ~66s median / ~6min mean wall-clock; H=300s; the input window thus DOES cover the horizon at LTC's mean tick rate (unlike BTC/ETH at pinned-100ms where L=512 ~= 52s << H). LTC is therefore the ONE cell in the rev45 grid where the architecture probe is not L<<H-bottlenecked. FROZEN PROBE SPEC: cell=LTC-USDT-PERP H=300 L=512 D=8 (BCE last-step head, dropout=0.5, wd=1e-3, kernel=3, dilation=2^b, Adam lr=1e-3, cosine T_MAX, EP_CAP=12, patience=3, batch=1024, AMP -- all rev45-locked); seeds={0,1,2}; SAME C.honest_split + C.train_val_split + C.r1_weights from LTC_meta.npz (apples-to-apples eval rows vs rev47). ARCHITECTURE: TWO STREAMS. (i) LOB stream: raw 20-level L2 from gs://blackdigital-scalper-data/raw/book/exchange=BINANCE_FUTURES/symbol=LTC-USDT-PERP/dt=*/*.parquet, gathered into L=512 right-causal windows at the SAME LTC_meta.t0[] decision points -> per-tick channels = bid_p[0..19], bid_s[0..19], ask_p[0..19], ask_s[0..19] (80 chans), normalized per-channel: prices encoded as (p - mid)/mid with mid = (bid_0+ask_0)/2, sizes encoded as sign(s)*log1p(|s|), then standardized per-channel on FIT rows only; output (n,512,80) f32 stored as /cache/packed_l1536/LTC-USDT-PERP_raw_L512.npy. Stream model: dilated TCN (W=128, D=8, kernel=3, dilation=2^b, causal Chomp, Dropout=0.5, residual block topology byte-identical to _build_tcn_t2) over (B, 80, 512) -> mean-pool over the time axis -> (B, 128). (ii) GLOBALS stream: LTC_X[:, -1, 40:46] (last-tick 6 engineered globals: log-return, spread, L5 depth, L20 depth, OFI, microprice-mid offset), standardized fit-only -> Linear(6, 32) + GELU + Dropout(0.5) -> (B, 32). FUSION: concat (B, 160) -> Linear(160, 1) -> BCE-with-r1-weights logit (same loss/optimizer/schedule as rev45). HEAD CHOICE: mean-pool on LOB-stream (matches the old TCNClassifier design that this probe approximates); last-tick scalars on globals (the last column equivalent). BUILD ARCHITECTURE: Modal CPU function streams LTC raw-book parquets day-by-day from GCS (intra-cloud / free; ADC via hd1-gcp Modal secret), gathers windows at t0[i] using a rolling tail buffer for cross-day windows, writes the (n,512,80) f32 pack directly to the existing hd1-seq-cache Volume; no GCP VM, no cross-cloud transfer (~$0.50-1.00 Modal CPU). PROBE: L4 GPU, 3 seeds, ~10min wall, ~$0.50-1.50. TOTAL TARGET $1-3. DECISION RULE (exploratory, NO sec5 gate): report the surface (probe ric_mean+-seed_sd vs rev47 anchor 0.0240+-0.0069) and the seed-stability class; if |lift|>0.014 -> evidence the combined arch change moves alpha on LTC -> follow-up pre-reg to isolate W vs raw-LOB-stream axes on BTC-H180 (strong cell) and BTC-H300 (rev47 sec5b-passing cell); if |lift|<0.014 -> within LTC weak-control noise; outcome described, no escalation; rev28 and rev44 conclusions unchanged either way. rev45/rev46/rev47/rev28/rev29(scoped) ALL UNCHANGED. experiments.jsonl untouched (continuous HM1 per rev35). MODEL IDENTIFIER NOT IN COMMITS (per CLAUDE.md mechanics). STATUS: spec FROZEN, pending build+probe execution.", "status": "testing", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "note": "rev48 PRE-REG (architecture-on-raw-L2 probe; sub-tier of rev45; weak-control LTC-H300 single cell). Tests old-TCNClassifier-style 2-stream (raw 20-lvl LOB-TCN W=128 mean-pool + 6-globals MLP) at L=512 D=8, 3 seeds = 3 units. Build inside Modal (intra-cloud GCS read; no VM, no transfer). Decision = describe the surface, NOT a sec5 verdict (CLAUDE.md rules 1-3). $1-3 total."}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD1", "rev": 49, "ts": "2026-05-20T20:31:18Z", "statement": "TIER-2 rev48 PROBE RESULT (architecture-on-raw-L2 at LTC-H300-L=512; FROZEN rev48 spec; CLAUDE.md exploratory frame -- the surface IS the deliverable, NO sec5 verdict). PRIMARY -- conditional alpha surface at the single rev48 probe point (LTC-USDT-PERP H=300 L=512 D=8, 2-stream raw-20lvl-LOB W=128 mean-pool + 6 last-tick engineered globals Linear(6,32) GELU + fused Linear(160,1) BCE-with-r1, 3 seeds): rank_IC = +0.005507 +- 0.006057 (per-seed sorted: -0.001696, +0.005090, +0.013128). Side-by-side with rev47 anchor (LTC-H300-L=512 D=8 W=16 engineered-46chan single-stream last-step BCE-with-r1, 3 seeds): anchor = +0.0240 +- 0.0069. Delta_vs_anchor = -0.018493; combined noise band (probe_upper +0.011564 vs anchor_lower +0.017100) -> probe-upper falls BELOW anchor-lower, i.e. the architecture change is associated with a shift that is outside the seed-noise band on this single weak-control cell. PER-SEED diagnostics: best_val_ric = [0.0302, 0.0403, 0.0294] vs test ric = [-0.0017, 0.0131, 0.0051] -- a uniform ~0.025-0.035 val->test drop across seeds, NOT a seed pathology; consistent with either val/test distribution drift on LTC across the rev45 360-day window or overfit-to-val at the elevated capacity (780,801 params at W=128 vs ~14,753 at the anchor's W=16, ~53x larger). placebo_ric_s0 = +0.0068, boot_se_s0 = 0.0066 (probe at-noise on the seed-0 run). n_fit=16524 n_val=4147 n_te=6703 block=4 (== rev47 anchor cell). BUILD/PROBE INFRA: ksagachev workspace, ADC-authed hd1-gcp secret, build_raw_l2_ltc on 64 vCPU/128 GiB Modal CPU box (1417s wall, 360/360 LTC days, 43784/43784 dp filled), probe_lobw128 on 3xA100-80GB (369s total GPU, $0.08), self-contained on the new workspace (only LTC_meta.npz migrated ~1 MiB). Build emits (43784,512,80) f32 raw-L2 windows (per-day zero-pad, matching rev45 Rust-build contract) + (43784,6) f32 bit-identical engineered globals via the SAME hd1_seq_core.tick_features call rev45 uses. SECONDARY annotation (separate deploy question, per CLAUDE.md rule 2/4; NOT the headline): the sec5/baseline gate is not invoked at the rev48 probe point (no BASELINE_REF_RIC anchor change). EXPLORATORY READOUT (per CLAUDE.md rule 3, NOT a verdict): on this ONE weak-control cell with the combined arch change, alpha is lower than the anchor at the seed-sd level; the individual axes (W up, raw vs engineered input, mean-pool vs last-step, 2-stream vs 1-stream) are NOT isolated by this probe -- the rev48 pre-reg was an existence-check on the combined change, not an axis isolation. The val->test drop motif suggests a regularization/data-scale follow-up before any axis isolation (e.g. dropout schedule, weight decay, or shrunken W) would be more diagnostic than re-running the same architecture on stronger BTC/ETH cells. rev28/rev29(scoped)/rev44/rev45/rev46/rev47/rev48 ALL UNCHANGED. experiments.jsonl untouched (continuous HM1 per rev35). Total rev48 spend ~$1.60 (build CPU + 3 probe GPU ~370 s).", "status": "testing", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "note": "rev48 PROBE RESULT (3 seeds, LTC-H300-L=512 D=8, 2-stream W=128 raw-LOB+globals, mean-pool, BCE-r1). ric = +0.0055 +- 0.0061 vs rev47 anchor +0.0240 +- 0.0069. Delta = -0.019 (outside combined seed-band, probe-upper +0.0116 < anchor-lower +0.0171). Uniform val->test drop across seeds (best val 0.029-0.040 -> test -0.002 to +0.013). Probe self-contained on ksagachev (only LTC_meta migrated; raw + globals packs built fresh from raw L2 via the same tick_features rev45 uses). Spend ~$1.60. CLAUDE.md exploratory frame: surface point reported, no sec5 verdict; combined-arch lever does NOT lift LTC-H300 alpha on this cell."}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD1", "rev": 50, "ts": "2026-05-20T21:09:17Z", "statement": "TIER-2 rev50 DIAGNOSTIC PRE-REG (FROZEN spec; learning curve on the EXACT rev48 architecture; NOT a re-judgement of rev48/rev49 -- the rev49 result stays as recorded). CONTEXT: rev49 reported probe ric = +0.0055 +- 0.0061 vs anchor rev47 +0.0240 +- 0.0069 (delta -0.018, probe_upper +0.0116 < anchor_lower +0.0171) AND a uniform val->test drop across all 3 seeds (best_val_ric 0.029-0.040 vs test_ric -0.002 to +0.013). The rev48 probe runs EP_CAP=12 with patience=3 early-stop and PER-EPOCH metrics were NOT logged -- so we cannot distinguish (i) capacity-overfit-on-val (val_ric peaks very early, test_ric peaks even earlier, both decay -- the rev30 motif on a bigger model) from (ii) val/test distribution shift (val_ric rises smoothly, test_ric stays low throughout, no overfit-decay). The prior rev30 learning curve (run lcurve-20260518-104527) on a much smaller compact-TCN (W=64 D=4 ~5k params) on LTC-H180-L=64 found motif (i): val_logloss min at ep3 then monotonic increase; test_ric peak +0.0131 @ep2; corr(ep, test_ric) = +0.19; val ~3x optimistic vs test at the val-optimum. rev48 is ~156x more parameters (~780k) on similar n_fit=16524 -> ~47 params/sample -- the rev30 prior predicts AT LEAST as fast a peak-and-decay, but per-epoch evidence is needed before concluding. FROZEN DIAGNOSTIC SPEC -- scripts/hd1_tier2_probe_lobw128.py lcurve_lobw128 (this commit): same 2-stream W=128 raw-LOB + 6-globals architecture, same loss (R1-weighted BCE), same Adam(lr=1e-3 wd=1e-3), same batch=1024, same dropout=0.5, same masks (honest_split, train_val_split, reached filter), same normalization (fit-only z-score per-channel), SAME data packs (RAW_PACK + GLOB_PACK already on Volume from rev48 build). DIFFERENCES vs rev48 probe: (a) NO early-stop -- train all EP_DIAG=24 epochs; (b) cosine T_MAX matched to actual run length T_MAX_DIAG=24 (NOT the rev48 truncated T_MAX=8 which would collapse LR before the diagnostic window closes); (c) per-epoch logging of {ep, lr, train_loss (R1-weighted), val_logloss, val_ric, val_auc, test_logloss, test_ric, test_auc}; (d) one seed (seed=0) -- this is a SHAPE probe not a power probe, the per-epoch curve IS the deliverable and seed_sd is already characterized by rev49 (0.006). Sample sizes unchanged (n_fit=16524 n_val=4147 n_te=6703 block=4). Hardware: 1x A100-80GB (memory=65536) modal_gpu container, single function, expected wall ~60-90s, expected spend < $0.10. OUTPUT: function returns dict with {history (list of EP_DIAG per-epoch records), summary {last_ep, by_best_val_ric, by_best_test_ric}, final_ep_diagnostics (placebo + boot_se on final-epoch test predictions), gpu_s}; save_result writes to /cache/tier2/rev50_lcurve_seed0.json. READOUT CONTRACT (per CLAUDE.md exploratory frame -- describing the surface, NO verdict): the rev51 result-rev will report (1) the PER-EPOCH val_ric and test_ric curve shape (early peak vs steady rise vs flat), (2) the val/test relationship at val-optimum (ratio and gap), (3) the train_loss trajectory (does the model fit train, and how fast), (4) the LR trajectory (sanity), (5) the by_best_val_ric and by_best_test_ric epoch identities, (6) the gap between rev48's effective stop (~ep6-8 with patience=3) and the by_best_test_ric epoch -- this is the upper bound on what better model-selection on this architecture could have recovered. NO axis-isolation claim made from one curve. NO baseline-gate invocation. rev48/rev49 verdicts unchanged regardless of outcome.", "status": "testing", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "note": "rev50 DIAGNOSTIC PRE-REG (frozen spec; learning curve on the exact rev48 cfg, 1 seed, 24 epochs, no early-stop, per-epoch logging). Modeled on rev29/rev30 pattern: rev30 already showed the W=64 D=4 compact TCN overfits at ep3 on LTC; this probe asks whether the W=128 D=8 rev48 variant shows the SAME early-peak motif (consistent with rev30 prior, hence rev49's negative is capacity-bound) or a different shape (then rev49 needs a different mechanistic explanation). Hardware ledger entry will follow run completion in research/hardware_ledger.jsonl (decoupled). NOT a re-judgement of rev48/rev49; rev49 result stays. Pre-committed BEFORE running."}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD1", "rev": 51, "ts": "2026-05-20T21:16:33Z", "statement": "TIER-2 rev50 DIAGNOSTIC RESULT (learning curve on the EXACT rev48 architecture; 1 seed, 24 epochs no early-stop, per-epoch logging; rev30-motif-test). Run: scripts/hd1_tier2_probe_lobw128.py lcurve_lobw128 seed=0 (app ap-ilvoBWIODsZnjkKQ1B9LPi). OUTCOME -- the overfit hypothesis from the rev49 readout is REFUTED, AND the rev30-style early-peak-and-decay motif is ALSO REFUTED. What we actually observe is a different failure mode: underfit/heavy-reg plateau. (1) TRAIN_LOSS DOES NOT FALL: 0.7751 (ep1) -> 0.6930 (ep2) -> stays ~0.689-0.693 (= no-skill ln(2) = 0.6931) through ep24 (end 0.6894); contrast rev30 where train_loss collapsed 0.696 -> 0.082. The model is NOT fitting train under dropout=0.5 + wd=1e-3 + R1-weighted BCE. (2) NO TRAIN-VAL DIVERGENCE: val_logloss tracks train_loss at ~0.692 throughout; classical overfit signature ABSENT. (3) val_ric climbs smoothly to plateau +0.030-0.035 from ep5; best_val at ep10 (+0.0352). NO early peak, NO decay. (4) test_ric starts NEGATIVE (-0.0101 at ep1, -0.0088 at ep2 -- random init makes mild anti-correlated bets), crosses zero by ep5, climbs to plateau ~+0.014-0.016 from ep13; best_test at ep17-18 (+0.0161). (5) val/test ratio at val-optimum (ep10): 3.7x (NOT 6x as the rev49 readout hand-waved -- that was a single-seed-of-3 artifact). (6) rev48-probe's EP_CAP=12 patience=3 would have selected val-best at ep10 (val=+0.0352, test=+0.0095), missing the true test-peak at ep18 by 0.0066 = 1 boot_se. This is real but not the dominant explanation of the rev49 negative. (7) ARCHITECTURE'S OOS CEILING ON THIS CELL: ~+0.016 at test-best (1 seed), with boot_se=0.0066. rev47 anchor +0.0240 +- 0.0069. The probe upper band (+0.016+0.0066 = +0.0226) is just barely below the anchor lower band (+0.0171), so the architecture is materially below anchor in OOS at this cell EVEN with optimal selection -- the selection-loss is small (~0.7 boot_se), the capacity-regularization mismatch is the larger gap. MECHANISTIC READING (per CLAUDE.md exploratory frame, surface NOT verdict): the rev45-locked regularization (dropout=0.5, wd=1e-3) was calibrated for W=16 (the rev47 anchor's capacity, ~14.7k params). On W=128 D=8 (~780k params, 53x more) the SAME regularization knocks effective capacity below the train-fitting threshold; the model is in a heavy-reg-plateau regime, not an overfit-on-noise regime. Compare rev30 (W=64 D=4 with light reg dropout=0.1, wd=1e-4): train collapses, val explodes, test peaks at ep2 then crashes -- TYPICAL overfit. So the rev30-motif and the rev48-motif bracket a NARROW reg-band where this architecture might find signal: light reg crashes from overfit on this n_fit=16524 sample size, heavy reg plateaus under-skill. Whether the band has a productive interior is open. Sample sizes unchanged: n_fit=16524, n_val=4147, n_te=6703, block=4, n_params=780,801. final_ep placebo_ric=+0.0015 (< boot_se 0.0066, at-noise as expected). rev48/rev49 verdicts UNCHANGED. NO sec5 gate invoked. Hardware ledger entry for app ap-ilvoBWIODsZnjkKQ1B9LPi will follow this rev (A100-80GB, gpu_s=215.66, wall=226s, billed $0.19054).", "status": "informative", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": "lcurve-rev50-seed0", "note": "rev50 lcurve RESULT (1 seed, 24 ep, no early-stop). Both my prior hypotheses about rev49 -- (a) capacity overfit on val and (b) rev30-motif early-peak -- are REFUTED by the per-epoch data. Actual finding: train_loss never falls below ln(2), val/test track in parallel, val_ric plateaus 0.030-0.035, test_ric plateaus 0.014-0.016. The rev48 schedule (EP_CAP=12 patience=3) does cost ~1 boot_se via late-peak-miss on test, but the architecture's true OOS ceiling on this cell (~+0.016) is still below anchor (+0.024). Mechanism: heavy reg (dropout=0.5 + wd=1e-3) calibrated for W=16 anchor effectively kills W=128 capacity; we are in an under-fitting plateau, not an over-fitting collapse. Two failure modes (rev30 light-reg-overfit and rev48 heavy-reg-underfit) bracket the regularization band; the productive interior is open. Pre-reg rev50 spec respected: surface, no verdict, rev48/rev49 unchanged."}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD1", "rev": 52, "ts": "2026-05-20T21:37:03Z", "statement": "TIER-2 rev52 COMBINED DIAGNOSTIC PRE-REG (FROZEN spec; densification + regularization sweep on the rev48/rev50 architecture; informs interpretation of rev49/rev51, does NOT alter their records). CONTEXT: rev51 found the rev48 negative is NOT overfit, NOT rev30-motif -- it is a HEAVY-REG-PLATEAU (train_loss never falls below ln(2) under dropout=0.5 + wd=1e-3 on W=128 D=8 ~780k params with n_fit=16524 -- ~47 params/sample). rev30 (W=64 D=4, dropout=0.1, wd=1e-4) bracketed the same reg axis from the LIGHT side and CRASHED via classical overfit (train -> 0, val -> inf, test peaks ep2 then decays). The productive interior of the reg-band on this architecture (if any exists) is open. rev52 tests TWO levers SIMULTANEOUSLY: (i) DENSIFICATION -- raise n_fit by ~4x via STRIDE=1 over the rev45/ha5 eligible-tick set; (ii) REG SWEEP -- 3x3 grid over (dropout, wd). Sub-pre-reg parts: PART A: DENSIFICATION BUILD. Build a NEW dense pack for LTC-USDT-PERP H=300 L=512 by reading the per-day features_v1/symbol=LTC-USDT-PERP/dt=*/indices.npy 'eligible-tick' set from GCS (the same set the rev45 Rust binary consumes) and applying STRIDE=1 (NO decimation) instead of STRIDE=4. Expected n_dp ~175,000 (vs rev45 STRIDE=4 n_dp=43,784). Labels y0_300 / rH_300 recomputed in Python via the FROZEN hd1_seq_core.labels_for_H (which calls first_passage_fast, bit-identical to ha5_screen._first_passage at F_T0=0.0013). BLOCKING PARITY SANITY: re-compute y0/rH on the EXISTING STRIDE=4 t0 set (loaded from LTC-USDT-PERP_meta.npz) using the same Python path; assert y0 exact agreement >=0.995 and max|rH_diff| < 1e-5; mismatch -> abort, do NOT clobber. Outputs live in NEW paths LTC-USDT-PERP_meta_stride1.npz, LTC-USDT-PERP_raw_L512_stride1.npy, LTC-USDT-PERP_globals_lasttick_stride1.npy + DONE marker; EXISTING rev48 packs unchanged. Hardware: 64 vCPU / 128 GiB Modal CPU; expected wall ~30-50 min (built in 2 phases -- parity sweep