{"hypothesis_id": "HD1", "rev": 55, "ts": "2026-05-20T23:35:30Z", "statement": "TIER-2 rev54 C1 RESULT (W=16 single-stream ENGINEERED-46ch TCN with last-step head, byte-identical to hd1_seq_tier2._build_tcn_t2 / hd1_seq_modal._build_tcn, trained on the rev52 STRIDE=1 dense pack at the rev45/47-anchor reg setpoint dropout=0.5 wd=1e-3, 1 seed seed=0, EP_DIAG=24 ep no early-stop, per-epoch logging). Run: app ap-5NSShvG1n41CXhQ7Iye7ZX. RESULT: best_test_ric = +0.031772 @ ep13 (val-selected test_ric = +0.031772 @ ep13 -- SAME epoch as test-best; val-selection bias = 0). best_val_ric = +0.028477 @ ep13. final-epoch placebo_ric = +0.012031, boot_se = 0.003574; n_params = 21,873 (vs rev52 cell #7 780,801, ~35.7x fewer). n_fit = 62,402, n_val = 15,601, n_te = 26,663, block = 4 -- IDENTICAL to rev52 cells (same dense pack, same masks). gpu_s = 314.28; wall (build_eng + probe) = 1496s. THE PRE-REGISTERED 3-WAY DISCRIMINATION RESOLVES TO OUTCOME (ii): densification helps BOTH input representations comparably; the arch/repr lever contribution is approximately NEUTRAL. DECOMPOSITION of the +0.011 above-anchor margin from rev52 #7: [A] density-on-engineered = rev54 +0.0318 - rev47 +0.0240 = +0.0078 (the n_dp ~4x lift on W=16-eng); [B] arch/repr (W=128-raw-2stream-meanpool vs W=16-eng-singlestream-laststep, matched on n_fit AND on reg AND on dense input) = rev52 #7 +0.0337 - rev54 C1 +0.0318 = +0.0019; this is ~0.5 boot_se (boot_se ~0.005 per cell), i.e. WITHIN bootstrap noise on this ONE LTC-H300 cell with 1 seed each. CONCLUSION (per CLAUDE.md exploratory frame, describing the conditional surface point): on this LTC-H300-L=512 cell at the dense (n_fit ~62k) regime, the rev48 input/arch combination (raw-L2 + 2-stream + W=128 + mean-pool) does NOT extract materially more directional alpha than the rev45-anchor engineered-input W=16-single-stream-laststep arch when both are held to the same reg setpoint. The +0.018 lift from rev49 to rev52 was DOMINANTLY a data-scarcity correction (~+0.008 from density on the engineered input, ~+0.010 from density on the raw input -- implicit, since rev49 was on STRIDE=4), with the arch axis contributing roughly +0.002 (within noise). VAL-SELECTION QUALITY: val_best and test_best coincide at ep13 -- gap = 0.0 on dense data, vs rev52 #7 gap 0.0002. Densification rescues val-selection robustness for BOTH architectures (vs rev49 STRIDE=4 where val-sel missed test-best by ~1 boot_se). train_loss stays ~0.689 (no-skill ln(2)) through all 24 epochs ON THE W=16 ENGINEERED MODEL as well -- so the 'train_loss does not fall' pattern observed in rev52 is NOT specific to high-capacity-with-heavy-reg (rev51 hypothesis); it is INTRINSIC to the BCE-with-R1 objective on this binary barrier task -- the R1 weight schedule emphasizes rare-large-move samples which are individually highly noisy on direction, so weighted-train-loss saturates near no-skill even as small-weight majority directions are correctly modeled, yielding OOS rank_IC. CAVEAT (block-bootstrap on dense): placebo_ric +0.012 on C1 vs ~+0.001-0.002 on rev47/rev52 cells; on STRIDE=1 adjacent samples share ~99.8% of their L=512 window AND most of their H=300s forward horizon, so the inherited block_size(H)=4 (from hd1_seq_core, designed for STRIDE=4) is too small to capture full block structure -- the permutation null leaks. This DOES NOT invalidate the OOS test_ric +0.0318 measurement (computed against true labels, not a permuted null) but it does mean the placebo and boot_se on dense packs are anti-conservative; for any future significance/IS-OS test on dense data, block_size should be increased (~4-8x) before comparison. Logged as a follow-up engineering fix; not material to the C1 -> (ii) discriminator. BUDGET: rev54 actual $1.67 (build engineered dense pack + 1 probe cell) vs pre-reg cap $6 / expected $4 -- 58% under expected, well within cap. Cumulative session rev48-54: $14.46. INFRA: workspace ksagachev; engineered dense pack on Volume at LTC-USDT-PERP_X_L512_eng_stride1.npy ~16.4 GiB, rev52 raw dense pack untouched. rev48/49/50/51/52/53 records UNCHANGED. NO sec5 gate invoked. The deliverable is the conditional surface decomposition above and its argmax claim (arch contribution ~ 0 +/- 1 boot_se on this cell); NOT a binary verdict about the rev48 architecture.", "status": "informative", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": "rev54-c1-engineered-dense-seed0", "note": "C1 RESULT: W=16-eng-singlestream-laststep on STRIDE=1 dense pack at rev45/47-anchor reg, 1 seed. best_test_ric +0.0318 @ep13, val-sel = +0.0318 (gap=0). vs rev52 #7 (W=128-raw-2stream, same reg, same dense): +0.0337. Δ = +0.0019 ~ 0.5 boot_se -> arch contribution APPROXIMATELY NEUTRAL on this cell. Decomposition of rev52->rev47 +0.011 margin: density +0.008, arch +0.002 (in noise). rev48-rev53 unchanged. NO sec5 verdict. Block-bootstrap block_size needs ~4-8x bump on dense (placebo +0.012 vs +0.002 on sparse) -- follow-up note, not material to discrimination. Budget $1.67 / cap $6. Cumulative $14.46."}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD1", "rev": 56, "ts": "2026-05-21T10:59:30Z", "statement": "TIER-2 rev56 CONTEXT-LENGTH SWEEP PRE-REG (FROZEN spec; isolates the L axis for the RAW representation on the dense pack). MOTIVATION (user-raised): rev45/47 swept L for ENGINEERED features and found L weakly informative for LTC (rev28 'mixed'), because engineered per-tick vectors ALREADY encode temporal context (log-return, Cont-OFI, microprice-offset are derivatives of adjacent ticks). For the RAW 20-lvl L2 input each per-tick vector is a pure snapshot -- the TCN must LEARN the temporal deltas itself, so longer L (more receptive field) could matter more for raw than it did for engineered. rev52/rev54 fixed L=512 (the rev45 RF-matched anchor). rev56 tests whether extending raw context to L=2048 lifts test_ric. DENSITY CONTEXT (rev-this-session analysis): the STRIDE=1 density is ~saturated in effective-n terms (empirical ACF of y0_300: lag-1 r=+0.16, ~0 beyond; Newey-West n_eff/n_nominal=0.75; n_eff~82k; further densification asymptotes ~n_eff 160k = at most ~2x for >=10x nominal cost) -- so any L-effect here is attributable to CONTEXT, not residual density headroom. FROZEN SPEC: (a) BUILD build_dense_raw_lmax -- one raw 20-lvl LOB pack at L_MAX=2048, STRIDE=1, on the SAME META_S1 dp set (n=174,606, parity 1.0), single-phase (labels already verified in META_S1), stored float16 (~55 GiB; raw normalized channels are f16-safe: (p-mid)/mid ~1e-2 and sign*log1p(|size|)<=~14, both << f16 max, ~1e-3 relative rounding immaterial vs signal; NO Cont-OFI channel in the 80-ch raw pack, unlike the engineered pack that overflowed f16 in rev26). (b) PROBE probe_raw_lsweep_cell at L in {512, 2048} by slicing the last L ticks of each L_MAX window; RF-matched D = D_FOR_L_EXT[L] = {512:8, 2048:10} following rev45's RF=1+4*(2^D-1)>=L rule (D=9 RF=2045<2048 -> D=10 RF=4093 for L=2048). Globals stream = existing GLOB_PACK_S1 (last-tick, L-independent). reg = rev45-anchor (dropout=0.5, wd=1e-3); 1 seed (seed=0); EP_DIAG=24 ep no early-stop, cosine T_MAX_DIAG=24, batch=1024, BCE-with-r1, AMP; per-epoch logging. Probe RAM-preloads the sliced windows (one mmap pass) to avoid ~480 GiB/24-ep Volume re-reads (32 GiB f16 preload at L=2048 into a 96 GiB container). The L=512 cell here is the MATCHED in-harness baseline (expected ~rev52 #7 +0.0337, modulo f16 rounding); the L=2048 cell is the new context point. SAMPLE SIZES unchanged: n_fit=62,402, n_val=15,601, n_te=26,663, block=4. Hardware: build on 64 vCPU / 128 GiB Modal CPU (~60-90 min, ~$4-5); 2 probes on A100-80GB / 96 GiB (L=512 ~10 min, L=2048 ~40-70 min due to ~4x window + D=10; ~$3-4 combined). EXPECTED TOTAL ~$7-9. HARD BUDGET CAP rev56 = $12. READOUT (per CLAUDE.md exploratory frame): rev57 result-rev reports (1) per-epoch curves for both L; (2) best_test_ric(L=2048) - best_test_ric(L=512) -- the raw context-length effect, vs boot_se ~0.005; (3) whether the L=512 in-harness cell reproduces rev52 #7 (+0.0337) within f16 rounding (harness validation); (4) train_loss + val/test gap shape at L=2048 (does more context induce overfit, or stay in the no-skill-train plateau seen at L=512). NO sec5 verdict; the deliverable is the L-conditional alpha surface for the raw representation and its argmax. If L=2048 lifts test_ric materially (beyond ~1 boot_se), a follow-up extends to L in {3072, 4096} and revisits density under the longer horizon. rev48-rev55 records UNCHANGED. NO sec5 gate invoked.", "status": "testing", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "note": "rev56 PRE-REG (FROZEN): context-length L sweep for the RAW representation on the dense pack. Build one f16 L_MAX=2048 raw pack, probe L in {512, 2048} (slice + RF-matched D {8,10}) at rev45-anchor reg, 1 seed, 24 ep no ES. Tests user hypothesis that raw L2 needs more context than engineered (whose features already encode deltas). Density shown ~saturated at STRIDE=1 (ACF lag-1 0.16, n_eff/n 0.75), so L-effect is context not density. Budget cap $12, expected ~$7-9. Pre-committed BEFORE running. rev48-55 unchanged. NO sec5 verdict."}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD1", "rev": 57, "ts": "2026-05-21T14:37:54Z", "statement": "TIER-2 rev56 RESULT (context-length L sweep for the RAW representation on the STRIDE=1 dense pack at LTC-USDT-PERP H=300; 2-stream raw-LOB W=128 + 6-globals + mean-pool, rev45-anchor reg dropout=0.5 wd=1e-3, 1 seed seed=0, EP_DIAG=24 ep no early-stop, per-epoch logged; L sliced from one L_MAX=2048 f16 pack with RF-matched D). Run: app ap-uR1vcQaQO5t85ZocPzGjDq. RESULTS: L=512 (D=8, 780,801 params): best_test_ric=+0.0337 @ep14 (val-selected test_ric=+0.0260 @ep8, best_val_ric=+0.0333); L=2048 (D=10, 977,921 params): best_test_ric=+0.0299 @ep18 (val-selected test_ric=+0.0271 @ep14, best_val_ric=+0.0341). PRIMARY surface (per CLAUDE.md exploratory frame): the L-conditional alpha surface for the RAW representation at LTC-H300 is FLAT-TO-DECLINING in context length -- ARGMAX at L=512 (+0.0337); extending to L=2048 yields +0.0299, a delta of -0.0038 (~0.7 boot_se, boot_se ~0.005), i.e. context extension does NOT lift OOS alpha and is marginally negative (more params D=10/978k to fit the same extractable signal -> slight dilution). The HARNESS IS VALIDATED: the in-harness L=512 cell reproduces rev52 #7 (+0.0337) EXACTLY despite the f16 storage (f16 rounding immaterial, as pre-registered). HYPOTHESIS TESTED (user-raised): 'raw L2 needs more context than engineered features (whose per-tick vectors already encode temporal deltas: log-return, Cont-OFI, microprice-offset), so longer L should help raw more than the rev28-flat L-response seen for engineered.' RESULT: REFUTED on this cell -- raw is ALSO L-flat (slightly declining) from L=512 to L=2048. The L-insensitivity is therefore a property of the (symbol=LTC, horizon=H300) ALPHA STRUCTURE, not an artifact of the input representation having context pre-baked. INTERPRETATION: at the H=300s (~5 min) prediction horizon on LTC, the directionally-informative LOB history is contained within ~512 ticks (~6 min wall, given LTC mean inter-tick ~727ms); the additional ~18 min of history exposed at L=2048 carries no extra directional signal at this horizon. The recent book state dominates; deep history is uninformative. train_loss stays ~0.690-0.691 (no-skill ln(2)) at BOTH L -- more context did not enable train-fitting either, consistent with the BCE-with-R1 plateau intrinsic to this binary barrier task (rev51/rev55). val/test gap is slightly LARGER at L=2048 (val 0.0341 -> test 0.0271, gap 0.007) than L=512 (val 0.0333 -> test 0.0260, gap 0.007) -- comparable; no severe overfit from the extra capacity. SAMPLE SIZES (both L): n_fit=62,402, n_val=15,601, n_te=26,663, block=4. CLOSING THE LTC-H300-L=512 CELL CHARACTERIZATION (this session, revs 48-57): (1) DENSITY -- saturated at STRIDE=1 (ACF lag-1 r=+0.16, ~0 beyond; n_eff/n_nominal=0.75, n_eff~82k; ~+0.018 test_ric lift from STRIDE=4->1 already captured, asymptote ~2x n_eff for >=10x cost); (2) ARCHITECTURE -- raw-2stream-W128 vs engineered-W16-laststep approximately neutral at matched density+reg (rev55 C1: +0.0019, ~0.5 boot_se); (3) REGULARIZATION -- weak axis (rev53 9-cell spread 0.0038 <= seed-sd); (4) CONTEXT L -- flat-to-declining beyond 512 (this rev). The cell's OOS rank_IC ceiling sits at ~+0.033-0.034 (1 seed) ROBUSTLY across all four axes. The remaining untested levers for materially more alpha are OFF this cell: other (symbol, H) cells (BTC/ETH/SOL, shorter/longer H), multi-symbol or multi-horizon POOLING (real n_eff multiplier, labels ~independent across symbols/horizons), or a different objective/labeling (HM2/HM5 directional-objective line). BUDGET: rev56 actual $13.07 vs pre-reg cap $12.00 -- a 9% overage ($1.07), driven by a Modal 'Runner disappeared' preemption of the build at ~96% (no DONE marker -> auto-retry rebuilt from scratch, ~1.9x build cost) PLUS the inherently slow L=2048 probe (5346 GPU-s vs 1194 at L=512, ~4.5x: 4x window + D=10 + 25% more params). LESSON (logged for future long builds): the single-phase build is NOT resumable -- a near