{"hypothesis_id": "HD1", "rev": 58, "ts": "2026-05-21T18:05:14Z", "statement": "ERRATUM (metadata correction; append-only, does NOT alter any conclusion). The recorded sample-size metadata in rev53, rev55 and rev57 statements/notes ('n_fit=62,402, n_val=15,601, n_te=26,663') was a back-of-envelope ESTIMATE mis-stated as exact. The ACTUAL probe-reported sizes on the STRIDE=1 dense pack (n=174,606, identical across rev52 9-cell sweep, rev54 C1, and rev56 L-sweep, read directly from the result JSONs) are: n_fit=65,727, n_val=16,448, n_te=26,692 (block=4 unchanged). The mis-statement is ~+5% on n_fit/n_val and ~0.1% on n_te. NO test_ric value, delta, argmax, boot_se, or qualitative conclusion changes -- those were computed by the probe on the TRUE splits; only the human-readable size annotations in the three result revs were wrong. Corrected values: the dense pack honest_split(174606) -> n_tr=122,224; the train-region reached fraction is higher than the global 62.4% (regime-dependent), so s_tr_all and its 80/20 fit/val carve give 65,727 fit / 16,448 val, with 26,692 reached test rows. All downstream comparisons (rev49 +0.0055; rev52 surface +0.031..+0.035 argmax drop=0.1/wd=1e-3 +0.0347; rev54 C1 +0.0318; rev55 arch-delta +0.0019; rev57 L=512 +0.0337 vs L=2048 +0.0299) stand UNCHANGED. A consolidated session SQLite (research/hd1_session_rev48_57.db: tables revs_summary/cells/epochs/hardware) is committed alongside this erratum and uses the CORRECT sizes (ingested from the result JSONs, not the prose). rev48-rev57 records otherwise UNCHANGED.", "status": "informative", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "note": "ERRATUM: rev53/55/57 stated n_fit=62,402/n_val=15,601/n_te=26,663 (estimate). ACTUAL (from result JSONs): n_fit=65,727, n_val=16,448, n_te=26,692. ~5% off on fit/val, 0.1% on test. NO conclusion changes. Consolidated SQLite research/hd1_session_rev48_57.db committed (correct sizes). Append-only: rev53/55/57 not mutated."}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD1", "rev": 59, "ts": "2026-05-21T19:43:42Z", "statement": "CHECKPOINT / SYNTHESIS (no new run; consolidates ALL HD1 TCN evidence to date into research/TCN_CHECKPOINT.md so we do not re-check settled axes. CLAUDE.md exploratory frame: conditional alpha surface is the headline; deploy-gate is a secondary annotation). AXES THAT MOVE ALPHA: (1) HORIZON -- strong, monotone H180>H300>H600 for every symbol & representation; (2) SYMBOL -- strong, BTC & LTC highest at short H, SOL lowest; (3) DATA DENSITY -- moderate then saturating (STRIDE=4->1 lifts LTC-H300 ~+0.008 to +0.018; n_eff saturates at STRIDE=1, ACF lag-1 0.16, n_eff/n 0.75). AXES THAT ARE ~NEUTRAL/WEAK (settled, do NOT re-run): input representation (46ch engineered ~= 80ch raw-LOB, Delta ~0.002 in noise, rev54/55); capacity W (16~=64~=128 under sane reg+data, rev51/53/55); regularization (3x3 dense grid spread 0.004 ~= seed-sd, rev53); context L (flat-to-declining beyond ~512 at H300; raw L512 +0.0337 > L2048 +0.0299, rev56; eng LTC-H300 flat 512-1536, rev46-47); head (last-step ~= mean-pool); streams (single ~= 2-stream); depth D (RF-match only, inert axis rev29). GLOBAL ARGMAX (most seed-stable alpha any TCN produced): BTC-H180, engineered-46ch, W=16 RF-matched L=512(D8), STRIDE=4 -> rank_IC +0.0389 +-0.0015 (rev47). Best on the LTC-H300 deep-dive cell: raw-80ch W=128 2-stream mean-pool dense(STRIDE=1) dropout=0.1/wd=1e-3 -> +0.0347 (1 seed), matching engineered-W16-dense +0.0318 within noise. CONDITIONS MAXIMIZING ALPHA: short horizon (H180) >> long; high-vol liquid symbol (BTC/LTC) > ETH > SOL; dense sampling STRIDE=1; context L>=512 (more does not help). Architecture / representation / capacity / head / streams are INTERCHANGEABLE at the alpha level -- TCN extracts the same ~directional component regardless. train_loss stays ~ln(2) at all W (intrinsic to BCE-R1 on this binary barrier task; OOS skill from small-weight majority direction, not memorization). DEPLOY ANNOTATION (secondary, separate question per CLAUDE.md rule 2/4): vs the HM6 snapshot XGBoost baseline, TCN ~= snapshot on SPARSE data (rev28 refuted, rev44 'TCN ~= snapshot fundamentally'; per-cell deltas near-zero/negative); the DENSE-data deploy comparison is NOT yet done (no dense baseline). OPEN (not checked): dense snapshot baseline; 3-seed validation of the dense cells; BTC-H180 (global argmax) on dense; multi-symbol/multi-horizon pooling (only identified real n_eff multiplier); directional objective (HM2/HM5 line); block_size bump for dense significance tests. Full detail + the per-cell surface tables in research/TCN_CHECKPOINT.md. Session cost rev48-58 = $27.53. rev25-58 records UNCHANGED; this is a pointer/synthesis, NOT a re-judgement.", "status": "informative", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "note": "CHECKPOINT: research/TCN_CHECKPOINT.md consolidates all HD1 TCN evidence. SETTLED (don't re-run): repr (eng~=raw), W (16~=128), reg (weak), L (flat>512 at H300), density (saturates STRIDE=1), under-training (ruled out rev30). ALPHA driven by horizon+symbol+density. ARGMAX BTC-H180 eng-W16-L512 +0.0389; LTC-H300 raw-W128-dense +0.0347. TCN~=snapshot on sparse (deploy, secondary); dense deploy untested. OPEN: dense baseline, 3-seed dense, BTC-H180 dense, pooling, directional objective. NOT a re-judgement; rev25-58 unchanged."}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD1", "rev": 60, "ts": "2026-05-21T19:51:58Z", "statement": "CHECKPOINT ECONOMIC-TRANSLATION ADDENDUM (no new run; corrects the rev59 checkpoint omission flagged by user -- rank_IC was recorded everywhere but never translated to the economic edge, which is the actual asset). FACTS (from experiments.jsonl, NOT estimated): rank_IC = AUC - 0.5; the TCN argmax BTC-H180 +0.0389 = AUC 0.539; LTC-H300 dense argmax +0.0347 = AUC 0.535; most cells AUC 0.51-0.53. The first-passage label barrier (+-0.13%) EQUALS the round-trip cost floor (0.13%), so a correct call nets ~0 and a wrong call loses ~26bp -> profitability needs win-rate well above ~60%, but AUC 0.54 implies ~52-54% -> deeply unprofitable. ECONOMIC GATE (ledger fields economic_pass_strict/loose): TCN HD1 = 0 of 12 cells pass (top-decile abs-move 0.13% = exactly cost floor); HM6 snapshot XGBoost baseline = 0 of 24 pass (AUC 0.51-0.55) -- the baseline is ALSO sub-economic, so 'TCN ~= snapshot' (rev28/rev44) means BOTH are sub-economic, NOT both good. Whole ledger: 13 of 100 pass, all in HA1/HA2/HA5/H3 (LINK/SOL), and the HM2 rev1 audit flagged HA1/HA5/H3 as magnitude/volatility-conflated objective artifacts (reg:squarederror on signed return rewards |move| not direction; HA5 0.70 AUC tautological vs a volatility target) -> the 'passes' are objective mis-specification, not clean directional alpha. BOTTOM LINE: across the entire TCN line (and its snapshot baseline) there is a faint, statistically-nonzero directional signal (AUC 0.51-0.54) that does NOT clear the 13bp cost floor by a wide margin; NO config is tradeable as a standalone directional predictor at this (label, cost) regime. The rev46-59 rank_IC surfaces are the conditional MAP of that sub-economic signal (where it concentrates: short-H, high-vol symbols, dense data) -- valuable for siting a future regime change, but not money as-is. GAP NOTED: the dense session (rev48-58) logged rank_IC ONLY; the decile-EV / win-rate / economic_pass fields were NOT computed for the dense cells (by AUC analogy they almost certainly fail too, but exact dense economic numbers are an open ~$0.5 eval re-run). IMPLICATION for next steps: representation/architecture/context/density tuning of the TCN is EXHAUSTED at the sub-economic ceiling (~AUC 0.54); the levers that could change the economic verdict are OFF the TCN-architecture axis -- (a) a directional OBJECTIVE instead of magnitude/MSE (HM2/HM5 line), (b) a wider barrier / lower-cost (maker-only) regime so the edge clears costs, (c) regime/event conditioning to trade only when the signal is strongest, (d) multi-symbol/horizon pooling for a real n_eff multiplier. research/TCN_CHECKPOINT.md sec0 updated with this translation. rev25-59 records UNCHANGED.", "status": "informative", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "note": "ECONOMIC TRANSLATION (user-flagged rev59 gap): rank_IC->AUC. TCN argmax AUC 0.539 (BTC-H180); LTC-H300 dense AUC 0.535. Label barrier 0.13% == cost floor -> need win-rate >>60%, AUC 0.54 gives ~52-54% -> unprofitable. economic_pass: TCN 0/12, snapshot baseline 0/24. Ledger's 13/100 passes are all HA1/2/5/H3 magnitude-conflated artifacts (HM2 audit), not clean direction. NO tradeable directional edge in the TCN line; rank_IC surface = map of a sub-economic signal. Dense economic numbers not computed (open ~$0.5 eval). Next levers OFF the TCN axis: directional objective, wider-barrier/maker regime, regime conditioning, pooling. rev25-59 unchanged."}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD1", "rev": 61, "ts": "2026-05-21T20:01:05Z", "statement": "FRAMING CORRECTION (no new run; user-flagged CLAUDE.md rule-3 violation in the rev60 economic addendum). PRIMARY (the asset, stated as the continuous surface): the HD1 TCN conditional alpha surface measures directional price-movement predictive skill as rank_IC (= AUC - 0.5), and it is REAL, SMOOTH, and CONDITION-DEPENDENT. Magnitude/where: AUC peaks ~0.539 at BTC-H180 (rank_IC +0.0389 +-0.0015, tight seed-band), ~0.535 on the LTC-H300 dense cell (+0.0347), ~0.51-0.53 on weaker cells. Drivers (the map): skill RISES with shorter horizon (H180>H300>H600 monotone), with higher-vol/liquid symbol (BTC/LTC>ETH>SOL), and with data density (STRIDE=4->1 adds ~+0.008..0.018 rank_IC); it is FLAT in context L beyond ~512 at H300 and ~invariant to representation (eng-46ch ~= raw-80ch), capacity (W16~=W128), reg, head, and streams. That what/where/how-much map IS the deliverable. CORRECTION: rev60 (and the first cut of TCN_CHECKPOINT.md sec0) led with the confirmatory deploy-gate -- 'AUC<0.54 -> sub-economic -> 0/12 pass -> not tradeable / not money' -- which is exactly the banned gate-collapse (CLAUDE.md rule 3: 'inert/no real effect/refuted/beats-baseline y-n' may NOT be the headline or lead). That output is destructive: it discards the continuous signal, which is the actual asset. Per CLAUDE.md rule 4 the fix is DEMOTION, NOT deletion: the frozen sec5 economic gate (first-passage +-0.13% barrier vs 0.13% cost floor; economic_pass_strict/loose) remains valid and recorded FOR THE CONFIRMATORY DEPLOY QUESTION ONLY, which this exploratory program is NOT asking and which NO result is expected to pass yet. It now appears solely as a clearly-labelled secondary annotation in TCN_CHECKPOINT.md sec0, never as the headline. The rev60 record stays (append-only) but its gate-as-headline framing is superseded by this rev for interpretation. The factual economic numbers in rev60 (AUC values, economic_pass tallies) are correct and retained as the secondary annotation; only their PROMOTION to headline was the error. rev25-60 records UNCHANGED; TCN_CHECKPOINT.md sec0 + sec3 reworded to lead with the skill surface.", "status": "informative", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "note": "FRAMING FIX (CLAUDE.md rule 3/4): rev60 wrongly led with the deploy-gate ('sub-economic / 0 pass / not money') -- the banned surface-collapse. PRIMARY restored: TCN directional skill surface is real & continuous, AUC peaks 0.539 (BTC-H180), driven by horizon+symbol+density, flat in L/repr/W/reg. The sec5 economic gate is DEMOTED to a labelled secondary annotation (valid for the confirmatory question only, not asked here, not expected to pass). rev60 numbers retained as annotation; only their headline promotion was the error. Checkpoint sec0/sec3 reworded. rev25-60 unchanged."}
{"compute_cost_usd": "~$20-40 (one pretrain ~6-12h on 1x GPU dominates; per-cell finetune is cheap). User sign-off 2026-05-21.", "compute_time": "$0 code+parity validation in the stdlib-only planning container; pretrain ~6-12h + finetune ~mins/cell on Modal/GCP.", "expected_lift": "unknown (exploratory surface, not a binary verdict). Prior HD1 from-scratch TCN H180 rank_IC ranges +0.018..+0.039 by symbol (BTC argmax +0.0389 +-0.0015). The SSL effect size hunted is O(seed-sd ~0.005-0.007), hence >=3 seeds x 4 cells for a robust read.", "hypothesis_id": "H7", "note": "FROZEN PRE-REG (do not mutate; correct via a new rev). DESIGN = fixed-backbone ablation: 2 arms differing ONLY in init -- init=ssl_pretrained vs init=random -- on ONE identical PatchTSTBackbone (src/ssl/model.py: num_channels=80 raw-L2 [bid_p,bid_q,ask_p,ask_q]x20, patch_len=16, stride=16, d_model=192, n_heads=8, n_layers=4, time_dim/L=256). Finetune head = mean-pool over (patches x channels) -> LayerNorm -> Linear(d_model->1), BCE-with-logits on R1 weights, up=1/dn=0 on 'reached' samples. EXTERNAL ANCHOR (no re-run): the ledger from-scratch W=16 TCN at the matched cell, to separate 'SSL gave representation' from 'SSL = regularization of an oversized model'. PARITY: labels/scope/split/metric REUSE hd1_seq_core VERBATIM (select_decision_idx STRIDE=4; labels_for_H first-passage +-0.13% F_T0; honest_split 70/30 EMB=64; train_val_split; r1_weights; auc->rank_IC=AUC-0.5; placebo_auc; block_bootstrap_auc_se; block_size; gate_cell/status_for_cell; BASELINE_REF_RIC). The ONLY DoF varied vs HM6 baseline_ref are model_family (patchtst_ssl / patchtst_scratch) and input_repr (raw_l2_20lvl); a hd1-parity assert runs before any sweep. CELLS = {BTC,ETH,LTC,SOL} x H180. SEEDS: >=3 finetune seeds/arm, shared across arms; ONE shared pretrained encoder (pretrain-seed variance is a KNOWN uncaptured term, add 3-seed pretrain later only if the signal is marginal). PRETRAIN CORPUS = Cryptolake raw/book pooled over the 4 symbols, dates STRICTLY before the EARLIEST test-window start across cells (= the train-region of the common-aligned ~360d range). This SSL-specific embargo is SEPARATE from the supervised honest_split and is the leakage source to guard. Record data_kind=real and init in {ssl,scratch} on each experiment row. DELIVERABLE HEADLINE = Delta rank_IC(SSL-scratch) surface by cell + argmax + seed-band (NOT 'SSL works y/n'). FALSIFICATION GATE for the hypothesis: Delta rank_IC > +1 block-boot SE AND consistent sign across >=3 of 4 cells. SECONDARY (demoted, deploy question only) = section-5 gate_cell vs BASELINE_REF_RIC. KNOWN RISK: H7 rev1 -- scripts/pretrain_ssl_transformer.py NaN'd after epoch 1; src/ssl/pretrain.py is a clean rewrite (grad-clip 1.0, RevIN, AdamW+cosine) but MUST reproduce a finite-loss epoch on a small slice before GPU spend (de-risk checkpoint). NEW CODE to write+validate $0 here, run on Modal/GCP: (1) Cryptolake raw/book 80-ch reader (LOBWindowDataset reads recorder flat-schema only); (2) decision-idx-aligned labeled finetune dataset; (3) thin head on PatchTSTBackbone (NOT the config-incompatible legacy src/models/patchtst.py classifier: patch16 vs 10, 80ch vs 60ch); (4) cells x seeds x 2-arm driver -> rank_IC/placebo/boot_se/gate -> experiment rows; (5) Modal/GCP runner. hardware_ledger.jsonl row on run.", "prerequisites": "H5 done; frozen scripts/hd1_seq_core.py; Cryptolake raw/book reachable; Modal/GCP access (pending, granted after prep); DE-RISK the prior SSL NaN-gradient failure (H7 rev1 note) before any GPU spend.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 2, "statement": "ALPHA (HD1-seq contract). Does SSL masked-LOB pretraining of a PatchTST encoder raise the OOS rank_IC surface vs a from-scratch-initialised IDENTICAL encoder, across the 4-symbol H180 row (BTC/ETH/LTC/SOL)? Deliverable = the Delta rank_IC(SSL - scratch) surface by cell + its argmax + seed-band; the frozen section-5 deploy-gate vs BASELINE_REF_RIC is a DEMOTED secondary annotation, never the headline. Re-frames H7 rev1 (old triple-barrier / execution-coupled framing) into the alpha/rank_IC search. Single pre-registered, frozen experiment.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-21T21:30:00Z"}
{"compute_cost_usd": "~$20-40 (GCP SOL build + slice on co-located VM = cheap intra-region egress; Modal pretrain ~one GPU-hour + finetune sweep). User sign-off 2026-05-21.", "compute_time": "<=4h end-to-end HARD CEILING (user constraint 2026-05-22): GCP build/stage ~50-75min + Modal pretrain+finetune ~2-2.5h.", "expected_lift": "unknown (exploratory surface). HD1 from-scratch TCN H180 rank_IC by symbol: BTC +0.0389+-0.0015, ETH +0.0244+-0.0005, LTC ~+0.030, SOL ~+0.018 (BASELINE_REF). Effect hunted ~ seed-sd 0.005-0.007 -> >=3 seeds x 4 cells.", "hypothesis_id": "H7", "note": "FROZEN PRE-REG rev3 (correct via new rev only). REPRESENTATION AMENDMENT vs rev2: use HD1's frozen 46-ch per-tick L2 transform (hd1_seq_core.tick_features, N_TICK_FEAT=46, 'raw_l2_20lvl'), L=256 -- NOT literal raw-80ch. Justification: (1) HD1 C1 rev54/55 established 46-ch ~= 80-ch raw for alpha (Delta~0.002, in-noise) -> quality-neutral; (2) direct comparability to the HD1 TCN surface + BASELINE_REF (same rep/labels/split/metric); (3) reuses the proven hd1_seq_modal.py build+train+ingest infra and the prebuilt tier2 pack; (4) fits the <=4h ceiling by avoiding a 250GB raw rebuild + cross-cloud egress. DEFERRED FOLLOW-UP (not lost): whether literal 80-ch raw gives SSL extra headroom over the 46-ch transform -- a later rev if this lands. DESIGN: fixed-backbone ablation, 2 arms differ ONLY in init -- init=ssl_pretrained vs init=random -- on ONE identical PatchTST encoder (channel-independent, F=46, patch_len=16/stride=16, d_model=192, n_heads=8, n_layers=4, L=256). Finetune head = mean-pool(patches x channels) -> LayerNorm -> Linear(d_model->1), BCE on R1 weights, up=1/dn=0 on 'reached'. PARITY: labels/scope/split/metric REUSE hd1_seq_core verbatim (select_decision_idx STRIDE=4; labels_for_H first-passage +-0.13%; honest_split 70/30 EMB=64; train_val_split; r1_weights; auc->rank_IC; placebo_auc; block_bootstrap_auc_se; gate_cell/status_for_cell; BASELINE_REF_RIC). Only model_family (patchtst_ssl/patchtst_scratch) and init vary. CELLS = {BTC,ETH,LTC,SOL} x H180. SEEDS >=3 finetune/arm, shared; ONE shared pretrained encoder (pretrain-seed variance a known uncaptured term). PRETRAIN CORPUS = pooled 46-ch windows of the 4 syms, rows with t0 STRICTLY before the earliest test-window start across cells (SSL-specific embargo, separate from honest_split). DATA PATH: GCP VM (co-located, cheap egress) builds SOL fresh (Rust hd1_seq_build / frozen path) + slices the prebuilt tier2 L1536 pack {BTC,ETH,LTC} to L256, repacks compact (f16) -> GCS hd1seq_ssl_pack/l256/; Modal downloads the compact pack (small egress), pretrains one encoder, finetunes 4x>=3x2. DELIVERABLE HEADLINE = Delta rank_IC(SSL-scratch) surface + argmax + seed-band (NOT y/n). FALSIFICATION GATE: Delta > +1 block-boot SE AND consistent sign across >=3 of 4 cells. SECONDARY (demoted) = section-5 gate vs BASELINE_REF_RIC. KNOWN RISK: prior SSL NaN-grad (H7 rev1) -> reproduce finite-loss epoch on a small slice before full pretrain. Modal GCS auth: workspace is fresh; stage pack via Modal Volume from the authed sandbox (no new long-lived SA key) OR create hd1-gcp secret -- decide at build. hardware_ledger.jsonl row on run.", "prerequisites": "H5 done; frozen hd1_seq_core; GCP authed (project-26a24ad0...) + Cryptolake reachable; Modal authed (workspace tg-bot-on, FRESH - no hd1-gcp secret yet); de-risk the prior SSL NaN-gradient failure before GPU spend.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 3, "statement": "ALPHA (HD1-seq contract). Does SSL masked pretraining of a PatchTST encoder raise the OOS rank_IC surface vs a from-scratch-initialised IDENTICAL encoder, across the 4-symbol H180 row (BTC/ETH/LTC/SOL)? Deliverable = Delta rank_IC(SSL - scratch) surface by cell + argmax + seed-band; section-5 deploy-gate demoted. AMENDS rev2 representation (literal raw-80ch -> HD1 frozen 46-ch raw-L2 'raw_l2_20lvl'); everything else in rev2 stands.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-22T00:40:00Z"}
{"compute_cost_usd": "~$15-20 (GCP build ~$1.5 + Modal A100 ~80min run + A10G smoke debugging). within the approved budget.", "compute_time": "<=4h ceiling honored: GCP build ~20min; Modal run ~80min (43min A100 pretrain on 535,593 pooled train windows + ~35min finetune 3 seeds x 2 arms x 4 cells).", "expected_lift": "measured: SSL adds rank_IC only on SOL (+0.0054, >1 seed-SE); ~0 within noise on BTC/ETH/LTC.", "hypothesis_id": "H7", "note": "SECONDARY ANNOTATIONS (demoted per CLAUDE.md, NOT the headline). (a) Pre-registered falsification gate (Delta > +1 block-boot SE AND consistent sign across >=3/4 cells): NOT met -- only SOL clears >1SE; positive-sign 2/4 -> SSL is not a robust row-wide lift, its benefit is concentrated on SOL. (b) Frozen section-5 deploy gate vs HM6 baseline_ref: 8/8 cells 'refuted' because this PatchTST rank_IC sits BELOW the HM6 XGB snapshot baseline (e.g. BTC 0.0213 vs baseline_ref 0.0419) -- a separate deploy question, expected, not the SSL question. (c) MODEL note: this PatchTST/L256 config underperforms both the HD1 TCN (BTC-H180 0.0213 vs TCN 0.0389) and the XGB snapshot -- a model-architecture observation; SSL was tested FIXED-BACKBONE (both arms identical PatchTST, only init differs) so the SSL delta is clean regardless of the absolute level. ARTIFACTS: research_runs/h7ssl-20260522-024422/results.json + 8 experiments.jsonl rows (kind=alpha, model_family=patchtst_ssl/patchtst_scratch). DEFERRED FOLLOW-UPS: (1) literal 80-ch raw repr (does SSL gain more headroom than on the 46-ch transform); (2) stronger pretext / more pretrain epochs (loss was flat -> SSL underfit); (3) why SOL (lowest-base cell) specifically benefits. Modal Volume h7-ssl-cache (~36GB pack + backbone) retained for these follow-ups; delete to stop storage cost if not pursued.", "prerequisites": "DONE.", "priority_rank": 20, "result_experiment_id": "h7ssl-20260522-024422_H7SSL_SOL-USDT-PERP_H180_ssl", "rev": 4, "statement": "RESULT (surface, headline). Delta rank_IC(SSL - scratch) on the 4-symbol H180 row is SYMBOL-CONDITIONAL. ARGMAX = SOL-H180: +0.0054 (> 1 seed-SE) -- SSL flips SOL from -0.0039 (scratch) to +0.0015 (ssl). The other three cells are within seed noise: BTC +0.000006, ETH -0.000075, LTC -0.00066 (all < seed-SD). SSL's benefit concentrates on the single weakest/lowest-base cell and is ~neutral where the from-scratch PatchTST already extracts signal (BTC +0.0213, ETH +0.0044). Pretrain masked-recon loss was nearly flat (1329->1308 over 8 epochs), foreshadowing a weak SSL signal. Closes the H7 rev3 pre-reg (run h7ssl-20260522-024422).", "status": "informative", "ts": "2026-05-22T04:35:00Z"}
{"compute_cost_usd": "smoke <$1 (1 H100, ~min); full tier provisional ~50-110 H100-hr, hard cap set post-smoke", "compute_time": "smoke ~minutes 1xH100; full tier TBD post-smoke calibration", "expected_lift": "exploratory - surface, not a point estimate; standalone rank_IC vs L per (sym,H) cell + seed-sd", "hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev1 PRE-REG (Mamba-2 SSD, streaming-stateful P2, 2-stream raw-L2 + 6 globals, BCE-R1). L-grid {6000,36000,216000} x H {180,600,1800} x {SOL,LTC} x seeds{0,1,2} = 54 units. STRIDE=1. Ensemble/orthogonality claim DEFERRED - this tier = standalone surface + persisted OOS preds. O(N) streaming (state-reset=L), Modal-preemption-resilient. pre-reg->smoke.", "prerequisites": "Modal H100; fp16 LOB tick-stream build (once); tests/test_hd1_parity-style parity assert on STRIDE=4 subgrid", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 1, "statement": "HD2 rev1 - MAMBA-2 STREAMING-STATEFUL TIER, PRE-REGISTERED & FROZEN (exploratory conditional-optimization, CLAUDE.md rules 1-3; spec frozen BEFORE build/run; model identifier kept out of all artifacts per CLAUDE.md mechanics). PARENT CLAIM (HD2): the Mamba-2 (SSD) architecture contributes directional signal valuable IN AN ENSEMBLE - i.e. ORTHOGONAL to the existing XGB-snapshot and TCN-seq members - NOT that it beats baseline standalone. Distinct from H1 (Mamba long-context, blocked) and NOT the HM3-descoped 'sequence-superiority' prior (HM3 covers standalone lift, not cross-model orthogonality). The ensemble/orthogonality test is DEFERRED (user 2026-05-21): this tier maps ONLY Mamba-2's standalone alpha surface and PERSISTS aligned OOS predictions (oof+test, per decision-point t0) for a later incremental-stacked-IC / pairwise-correlation test vs separately-run XGB & TCN members. PRIMARY DELIVERABLE (rule 1, headline ALWAYS): OOS rank_IC mean +/- seed-sd as a function of usable context L per (symbol,H) cell; the L maximizing alpha per cell, its magnitude & seed-stability. delta-vs-baseline / sec5 gate is SECONDARY (rules 2/4) AND cross-window here (tier=500d STRIDE=1 vs HM6 baseline_ref=360d STRIDE=4) so sec5 is NON-BINDING this tier; reported for context only, never as framing. FROZEN AXES: * MODEL: pure Mamba-2 (SSD), mamba_ssm CUDA kernels (NOT pure-PyTorch). 2-STREAM, mirroring rev48 input contract: (i) LOB stream = raw 20-level L2 per tick = 80 channels [bid_p0..19, bid_s0..19, ask_p0..19, ask_s0..19], normalized per-channel prices (p-mid)/mid, sizes sign*log1p(|s|), standardized on FIT-region ticks only -> Mamba-2 stack -> hidden state read at decision points; (ii) GLOBALS stream = 6 last-tick engineered globals = hd1_seq_core.tick_features cols [40:46] (mid log-ret, rel spread, L5 depth-imbalance, L20 depth-imbalance, Cont OFI, microprice-mid offset), bit-identical to the frozen transform, standardized fit-only -> Linear(6,32)+GELU+Dropout. FUSION concat -> Linear->1 -> BCE-with-R1 logit. Mamba-2 hyperparams (d_model, n_layers, d_state, expand, dropout, wd, lr, schedule) pinned at smoke-calibrated values and recorded in the result rev BEFORE the full sweep (frozen post-smoke, pre-full). * CONTEXT L (swept architecture axis / surface locus) in {6000, 36000, 216000} ticks (~10min / 1h / 6h at SOL ~103ms median tick). * HORIZON H in {180, 600, 1800} s. * SYMBOLS {SOL-USDT-PERP, LTC-USDT-PERP}; window = most-recent 500 COMMON calendar days where BOTH are gap-free in features_v1 + raw/book (exact dates pinned at build, recorded). Cross-symbol consistency judged on the matched set. * SEEDS {0,1,2}. STRIDE=1 (decision points = full features_v1 ~24s grid, no decimation; user 2026-05-21 - recent experiments show STRIDE=1 best). * UNITS = 2 sym x 3 H x 3 L x 3 seeds = 54 training runs (L=surface axis, seeds=stability axis). FROZEN STREAMING-STATEFUL SEMANTICS (P2, the optimization core): * One causal forward pass per (symbol, contiguous gap-free day-segment); NO overlapping windows. * State carried across fixed sub-chunks of C=2048 ticks; gradient detached at sub-chunk boundaries (TBPTT). State RESET to learned-init every L ticks -> L = max usable context (the knob). Compute = O(total_ticks) INDEPENDENT of L; memory = O(C). * WARMUP-FLOOR: within each L-reset-period the first min(L,2048) ticks build state with NO loss/readout; ALL decision points past the warmup are scored (readout+loss) - PRESERVES STRIDE=1 density (interacts with the STRIDE=1 choice: score-late >=0.75L would discard most STRIDE=1 points, so rejected). Context-at-scored-point in [2048, L]; its per-cell distribution recorded. * REPORT rank_IC on BOTH (a) all OOS scored points and (b) the deep-context subset (context >= 0.75*L) to isolate the L effect from intra-period heterogeneity. FROZEN PARITY (BINDING, pre-sweep): label/scope/split/R1-weight/AUC/placebo/block-bootstrap-SE bit-parity with hd1_seq_core (first-passage F_T0=0.0013; honest 70/30 + EMB=64; train_val 80/20; block_size(H) at STRIDE=1). Because STRIDE=1 (vs frozen default 4), the parity gate asserts y0/rH bit-exact agreement on the STRIDE=4 SUB-GRID of the STRIDE=1 t0 set vs the frozen functions (y0 frac >=0.995, max|rH_diff|<1e-5); mismatch = BUILD BUG -> ABORT, no sweep. The 6 globals come from the frozen tick_features cols [40:46] verbatim. n_eff caveat (recorded): STRIDE=1 is a TRAINING-DENSITY lever (~4x decision points, n_dp~488k/SOL-500d), NOT statistical-power inflation - block-bootstrap block_size absorbs the added autocorrelation; significance judged on n_eff, unchanged by density. DATA PIPELINE (build-once, separate from train, preemption-isolated): raw/book parquet -> normalized fp16 80-ch tick-stream + gap segmentation + decision-point t0 index (features_v1 indices, STRIDE=1) + per-H labels/rH/R1 (via frozen core) -> memory-mappable per-(symbol,day) arrays on a Modal Volume (~35 GB SOL+LTC, vs TB-scale windowed packs). Builder parallel over days (all cores; Rust-port candidate for parity with the existing cache stack). Built once; all 54 runs read it. HARDWARE / PREEMPTION (Modal H100, assume preemptible-only / constant interruption): idempotent units = (cell, seed, L, day-shard) in a Volume manifest; atomic checkpoint {model,opt,sched,RNG,data-cursor} every N steps (write-temp->rename, keep last-2) + SIGTERM-flush; Modal .map/.spawn high retries auto-reschedules preempted containers, resuming from cursor - preemption costs <=minutes, never corrupts. GPU efficiency: real Mamba-2 Triton kernels, bf16 autocast (SSM state fp32), sequence-packing to ~85% VRAM, gradient-checkpointing for the L=216000 cell, multi-GPU DDP over shards. EXECUTION ORDER (user 2026-05-21: pre-reg->smoke): SMOKE FIRST = 1 day SOL, 1 seed, tiny model, 1 H100 - validates data->kernel->state-carry->loss->atomic-checkpoint/resume->parity-assert, AND measures real H100 tokens/s to project exact full-tier H100-hours. Provisional full-tier envelope ~50-110 H100-hr; the HARD COST CAP is set from the smoke-calibrated projection and signed off BEFORE the full 54-run sweep (CLAUDE.md cost-gate; no full sweep auto-launched). experiments.jsonl untouched until results land. baseline_ref = HM6 rev4 for H in {180,600} (cross-window, secondary); H=1800 has NO baseline -> standalone surface only. STATUS: spec FROZEN, pending smoke build+run.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-22T19:14:22Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev2 RESULT: long-context surface. LTC monotone-rises-with-L (argmax 216000/6h, H180 0.0499>HM6 0.0378 cross-window), SOL weak/non-monotone. Cross-symbol-inconsistent -> HM1 marginal, sub-economic. Ensemble/orthogonality claim DEFERRED (preds persisted). Infra right-sized to L4 post-hoc.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": "hd2-20260523_LTC-USDT-PERP_H180", "rev": 2, "statement": "HD2 rev2 - TIER RESULT: Mamba-2 streaming-stateful long-context surface (run hd2-sweep 2026-05-23; 18 units = 2 sym x 3 L x 3 seeds, multitask-H; 500 common days 2024-12-25..2026-05-08; STRIDE=1; frozen-core parity; 6 alpha rows hd2-20260523_* ingested, exploratory). PRIMARY DELIVERABLE - conditional alpha surface rank_IC(L) per (symbol,H), seed mean+-sd (CLAUDE.md rule 1, headline): LTC-USDT-PERP: rank_IC RISES MONOTONICALLY with usable context L at EVERY horizon, seed-stable (sd<=0.003): H180 0.0411->0.0491->0.0499 (L 6k->36k->216k), H600 0.0194->0.0276->0.0290, H1800 0.0074->0.0097->0.0122; argmax L=216000 (~6h) for all 3 LTC horizons - the long-context axis is a real seed-stable lever on LTC, the receptive-field regime the HD1 TCN could not reach. SOL-USDT-PERP: weak and NOT monotone - H180 0.0130->0.0135->0.0149, H600 ~0.006 noisy (seed-sd .008-.014), H1800 best at L=6000 (0.0233+-0.002) DECREASING with L; no clean context lift on SOL. SECONDARY (deploy-distance, NOT framing; rules 2/4): delta_ic vs HM6 baseline_ref is CROSS-WINDOW (500d STRIDE1 vs HM6 360d STRIDE4 -> sec5 NON-BINDING per rev1); with that caveat LTC-H180 L=216000 (0.0499) exceeds HM6 (0.0378) by +0.0121 (>seed-sd), LTC-H600 +0.0033; SOL cells below HM6 (-0.007..-0.010). BOUNDED READOUT (rule 3, NOT a verdict): long-context Mamba-2 surfaces a seed-stable monotone context-length effect ON LTC reaching/exceeding the snapshot baseline at 6h - the first representation in the program to move above snapshot on a symbol - but CROSS-SYMBOL-INCONSISTENT (weak/absent on SOL), so by HM1 a symbol-specific marginal, not a robust both-symbol effect; magnitudes sub-economic (rank_IC ~0.05, move<cost floor). HD2 PARENT CLAIM (Mamba-2 contributes ORTHOGONAL signal IN AN ENSEMBLE) NOT yet tested: OOS preds (per-t0) persisted to Volume results/hd2/*_preds.npz for the deferred incremental-stacked-IC / pairwise-correlation test vs separately-run XGB & TCN members - that is the actual HD2 question, still OPEN. INFRA/COST: right-sized post-hoc - smoke showed ~5GB footprint so H100 ran at ~6% VRAM (wasteful); sweep code moved to L4 24GB + per-L token-budget batch-fill for all future runs. Tier spend ~5-35 (build+smoke+sweep). NEXT (user-owned): (a) run the orthogonality/ensemble test (the parent claim); and/or (b) re-test the LTC-monotone-L effect on a common-window vs in-run snapshot baseline to convert the cross-window delta into a clean sec5 both-symbol comparison.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-22T21:11:16Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev3 RENAME: HD2 name -> 'Mamba 2 finds a trading signal' ('Mamba 2 nakhodit torgovyy signal'). rev1/rev2 unchanged (append-only). Clarifies framing + de-confuses from HD1/TCN; stays exploratory surface (NOT the HM3-descoped binary); ensemble/orthogonality demoted to downstream.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 3, "statement": "HD2 rev3 - HYPOTHESIS RENAMED for clarity (user 2026-05-23). The human-readable NAME of HD2 is now 'Mamba 2 nakhodit torgovyy signal' / 'Mamba 2 finds a trading signal' - i.e. does the Mamba-2 (SSD) architecture detect harvestable DIRECTIONAL signal on crypto-futures LOB. This REPLACES the prior narrower headline framing ('Mamba-2 contributes ORTHOGONAL signal in an ensemble', rev1/rev2) as the NAME, to stop confusion with HD1 (the TCN line) and to match what the tier actually measured (the standalone alpha surface). APPEND-ONLY: rev1 (pre-reg) and rev2 (result) are UNCHANGED and remain the substantive record; this rev fixes name/framing only, adds no new run. METHODOLOGY NOTE (so the rename is not misread): 'finds a signal' does NOT revert to the binary 'sequence beats snapshot' question that HM3 descoped as an accepted prior. HD2 stays an EXPLORATORY conditional-optimization surface (CLAUDE.md rules 1-3): WHERE / HOW MUCH / how seed-stable is the signal across the swept conditions (context L, symbol, horizon H) - a response surface, not a beat/no-beat verdict. CURRENT EVIDENCE (rev2, unchanged): the standalone rank_IC(L) surface shows Mamba-2 DOES find directional signal that RISES monotonically with usable context on LTC (argmax L=216000/6h; LTC-H180 0.0499 > HM6 snapshot 0.0378, cross-window secondary), seed-stable (sd<=0.003); SOL weak/non-monotone; cross-symbol-inconsistent (HM1 marginal) and sub-economic (rank_IC ~0.05, top move < 0.13% cost floor). So as named: Mamba-2 finds a trading signal = YES in the weak statistical sense on LTC (and it scales with context, the TCN-unreachable regime), NOT YET in the economic/deployable sense. Whether that signal is decorrelated from XGB/TCN and useful in a stack is now a DOWNSTREAM sub-question, not the headline; OOS preds persisted for it (HF delmiron27/scalper-bot-hd2-results + Modal Volume). Data account-portable on HF: cache delmiron27/scalper-bot-hd2-cache, results delmiron27/scalper-bot-hd2-results (both private). 6 alpha rows hd2-20260523_* and hypothesis_id 'HD2' UNCHANGED (id is the stable key; only the name/statement evolves). STATUS testing (open).", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-22T22:26:54Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev4 NAME: HD2 -> 'Under what conditions does Mamba-2 yield the most alpha' (exploratory conditional-optimization, response-surface unit; supersedes rev3 'finds a trading signal'). rev1/rev2/rev3 unchanged (append-only). Goal 'make Mamba-2 as strong as possible' formalized as the conditions->alpha surface, per CLAUDE.md default mode.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 4, "statement": "HD2 rev4 - NAME FINALIZED (user 2026-05-23): the name of HD2 is 'Pri kakikh usloviyakh Mamba 2 dayot maksimum alpha' / 'Under what conditions does Mamba-2 yield the most alpha'. This SUPERSEDES the rev3 name ('Mamba 2 finds a trading signal') because HD2 is an OPTIMIZATION/research track, not a binary claim - the honest goal is 'make Mamba-2 as strong as possible', and the falsifiable, non-aspirational way to state that (per CLAUDE.md, the DEFAULT mode for architecture research) is EXPLORATORY CONDITIONAL-OPTIMIZATION: the unit is the QUESTION 'under what conditions (context L, hyperparams, data scale, objective, symbol, horizon) does Mamba-2 yield the MOST alpha, how large, and how seed-stable', and the DELIVERABLE is a RESPONSE SURFACE - not a yes/no verdict. (Same framing as HD1/TCN: a research track, not one falsifiable hypothesis.) APPEND-ONLY: rev1 (pre-reg), rev2 (result), rev3 (rename) are UNCHANGED; hypothesis_id 'HD2' and the 6 alpha rows hd2-20260523_* are UNCHANGED (id is the stable key). CURRENT SURFACE (rev2, the FIRST swept axis = context L): Mamba-2's alpha RISES monotonically with usable context on LTC (argmax L=216000/6h; LTC-H180 rank_IC 0.0499 > HM6 snapshot 0.0378, cross-window secondary), seed-stable; SOL weak/non-monotone; cross-symbol-inconsistent (HM1 marginal), sub-economic. AXES STILL TO SWEEP to push the surface toward 'maximum alpha' (each a future sub-tier, NOT yet run): model capacity (d_model/depth/d_state) + regularization, training-data scale, the R0-R4 objective/loss family (HM5), more/other context encodings, and the downstream ensemble/orthogonality use (preds persisted: HF delmiron27/scalper-bot-hd2-results). STATUS testing (open).", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-22T22:35:40Z"}
{"compute_cost_usd": "~$30-35 (mid pass ~$8 + L4 screen ~$25)", "expected_lift": "exploratory - rank_IC(target-form) surface; pick the barrier/form that maximizes seed-stable rank_IC subject to >=cost economic guard", "hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev5 PRE-REG objective round 1 = BARRIER/TARGET-FORM (upstream of R0-R4). ~10 variants: FP-width {0.08,0.13,0.20,0.30} + asym + vol-scaled + terminal/deadband/vol-norm. mid+ts pass unlocks train-time relabel. screen 1seed/L216k/both-sym, select rank_IC+econ-guard, confirm 3 seeds. user GO.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 5, "statement": "HD2 rev5 - OBJECTIVE-AXIS sub-tier 1 PRE-REG (FROZEN; greedy staged search, user GO 2026-05-23): sweep the BARRIER / TARGET-FORM first (the upstream, more fundamental knob), freeze the best, THEN the loss/weighting round (R0-R4 + focal/soft-rank-IC/...). RATIONALE: R0-R4 (HR1) vary ONLY loss-weighting on a FIXED +-0.13% first-passage label; the barrier/target-FORM (what counts as a tradeable move) is a separate, economically-linked, never-on-sequence axis (HA7 T-family was XGB-snapshot only). INFRA UNLOCK: the stream cache stored only +-0.13 labels + terminal r_H, NOT the mid-path (normalized LOB loses the mid level); a one-time build_mid pass (/cache/midts/{sym}/{day}.npz = per-tick ts+mid from raw/book bid_0/ask_0/timestamp) enables train-time relabeling at ANY barrier/form via the FROZEN hd1_seq_core.labels_for_H / first_passage_fast (parity preserved). FROZEN VARIANTS (~10): first-passage SYMMETRIC f in {0.08, 0.13(control), 0.20, 0.30}%; FP ASYMMETRIC {+0.13/-0.20, +0.20/-0.13}; VOL-SCALED FP f_i={1.0,1.5}*sigma_local (sigma = trailing mid-logret std, per-sample barrier); TERMINAL sign(r_H); TERMINAL deadband |r_H|>0.13%; TERMINAL vol-norm sign(r_H/sigma). SCREEN (rank many cheap, rev52-style landscape): 1 seed (seed=0), BOTH symbols, multitask H={180,600,1800}, L FROZEN=216000 (rev2 argmax), all model HPs at CURRENT (d_model=256, d_state=128, n_layers=4, d_conv=4, expand=2, dropout=0.1, wd=1e-3, R1 |move|-weighted BCE loss - loss is the NEXT round, held fixed here). SELECT: rank by mean OOS rank_IC over the 6 (sym,H) cells (seed0) WITH an economic guard - reached-rate not degenerate AND top-decile |move| >= 0.13% cost floor; a target-form that maximizes rank_IC on sub-cost noise is REJECTED (HM1 spirit: statistical-but-sub-cost is worthless). CONFIRM: the winning target-form re-run on 3 seeds -> seed-mean+-sd, frozen as the HD2 target for the loss/weighting round. EXPLORATORY (CLAUDE.md rules 1-3): deliverable = rank_IC(target-form) surface + argmax + seed-stability, NOT a verdict; sec5 gate non-binding. COST ~$30-35 (mid pass ~$8 + screen ~10 variants x2 sym on L4 ~$25), new spend, user GO. rev1-4 UNCHANGED (append-only); hypothesis_id HD2 + 6 alpha rows unchanged. STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-22T23:19:34Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev6 RESULT+FREEZE: barrier round done. FREEZE +-0.30 FP (skill == +-0.13 per 3-seed confirm, but economically dominant: breakeven 68% vs 92%). User corrections: asym_up excluded (inflates), rank_IC!=economic value. Skill still the wall (net-neg at current AUC~0.52). -> R2.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 6, "statement": "HD2 rev6 - OBJECTIVE round 1 (barrier/target-FORM) RESULT + DECISION (rev5 frozen spec; exploratory surface, CLAUDE.md rules 1-3). Screen ~13 forms x {SOL,LTC} x seed0, L=216000, R1 loss, model HPs at current; + 3-seed confirm of the top symmetric pair. TWO USER METHODOLOGY CORRECTIONS folded in: (1) fp_asym_up (+0.13/-0.20) EXCLUDED from selection - the NEAR barrier on the predicted-positive side inflates rank_IC via labeling skew (mechanically easier to be 'right up'), not real directional alpha; fp_asym_dn (+0.20/-0.13, conservative, ~deploy R:R 1.5:1) RETAINED. (2) rank_IC is SKILL-only / PAYOFF-BLIND - barrier width is NOT economically inert: breakeven hit-rate p*=(1+c/f)/2 with c~0.11% maker round-trip = 92%@+-0.13, 78%@+-0.20, 68%@+-0.30 -> a wider barrier needs far lower accuracy to break even AND pays ~2.3x more per correct call at FIXED cost. SURFACE (mean rank_IC /6 cells, seed0; LTC strong, SOL weak as throughout): fp_asym_up 0.023(excl), fp_0.30 0.0218, fp_0.13 0.0205, terminal 0.0195, fp_asym_dn 0.0181, fp_0.20 0.0179, fp_0.08 0.0161, fp_vol_1.5 0.0160, deadband_0.13 0.0139, fp_vol_1.0 0.0129, volnorm 0.0100. CONFIRM (seeds 0,1,2): fp_0.30 +0.0214+-0.0018 vs fp_0.13 +0.0195+-0.0026 - directional SKILL STATISTICALLY EQUAL across barrier width (delta +0.0019 within seed-sd, bands overlap). DECISION (user 2026-05-23): FREEZE the +-0.30% symmetric first-passage barrier as the HD2 target for all subsequent rounds - same skill as +-0.13 but economically dominant (breakeven 68% vs 92%, 2.3x payoff). HONEST BOUND: at current skill (AUC~0.52) ALL barriers remain net-negative (edge << cost); a wider barrier lowers the skill-bar toward achievable but does NOT itself create profit - skill stays the binding constraint (consistent w/ the MFE-MAE symmetry wall: wider scales symmetric win/loss tails equally, only real direction monetizes). SOL weak at EVERY form -> target-form does NOT fix cross-symbol-inconsistency. fp_sqrt (sqrt(H)-scaled, H-matched barrier; user H-coupling point) = supplementary probe, partial at write, does not affect the freeze. INFRA: train-time relabel via build_mid (/cache/midts ts+mid from raw/book) + hd2_targets.make_target, parity via frozen hd1_seq_core.first_passage_fast. rev1-5 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-23T16:39:55Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev7 PRE-REG R2 = loss/weighting on frozen +-0.30. ~8 variants incl user's magnitude/asym reward + IC/soft-rank + Huber; MSE excluded (HM2). screen 1seed/L216k/both-sym -> confirm 3 seeds -> freeze objective.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 7, "statement": "HD2 rev7 - OBJECTIVE round 2 (LOSS/WEIGHTING) PRE-REG (FROZEN; greedy chain: barrier +-0.30 frozen at rev6, now sweep the TRAINING OBJECTIVE). TARGET FROZEN: +-0.30% symmetric first-passage (rev6 decision). CENTERPIECE = the user's magnitude-and-sign-aware reward ('bigger favorable move -> bigger reward, bigger adverse move -> bigger penalty'). FROZEN LOSS VARIANTS (~8), all on the frozen +-0.30 label/eval: R0 plain BCE (control) · R1 BCE x |r_H| clip-p99 (current default) · R2_econ BCE x max(|r_H|-cost,0) · focal (gamma=2) · asym BCE with wrong-DOWN penalty > wrong-up (risk-averse, user's idea) · label_smooth BCE(ls=0.05) · IC/soft-rank: maximize soft-Spearman(pred, r_H) (optimize the REPORTED metric directly) · huber_ret: Huber regression on r_H then sign (robust). Continuous variants (IC, huber) train on r_H but are EVAL'd by the SAME +-0.30 directional rank_IC for comparability. SCREEN: 1 seed, both symbols, multitask H={180,600,1800}, L=216000, all model HPs at current (d_model=256,d_state=128,n_layers=4,d_conv=4,expand=2,dropout=0.1,wd=1e-3). SELECT: mean OOS rank_IC over the 6 cells (the +-0.30 directional skill) + seed-stability; the loss maximizing seed-stable skill wins -> confirm 3 seeds -> freeze as the HD2 objective for the capacity rounds. BINDING CAVEAT (HM2): naive MSE-on-return is magnitude-DOMINATED (huge moves drown small-move direction) -> EXCLUDED; magnitude-awareness implemented only via clip / rank / Huber. EXPLORATORY (rules 1-3): surface = rank_IC(loss-variant), not a verdict; sec5 non-binding. COST ~$5-7 (L4, ~16 screen units + confirm). rev1-6 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-23T16:39:55Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev8 TARGET CORRECTION (user): drop barrier-as-target; HD2 target = continuous unbounded r_H (rank-IC), per goal + PLAN.md. barrier round (rev5/6) kept as informative detour. R2 re-scoped to continuous r_H.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 8, "statement": "HD2 rev8 - TARGET CORRECTION (user 2026-05-23): the rev6 freeze of the +-0.30 barrier AS THE TARGET is SUPERSEDED. A first-passage barrier is a CAPPED, execution-laden event (TP/SL at +-f): it (a) discards move magnitude beyond +-f and (b) bakes in an exit assumption - both contradict HD2 goal (execution-neutral, MAXIMIZE alpha) and the program canonical alpha metric (PLAN.md: target = forward log-return r_h, metric = OOS rank-IC; HA1 used exactly this). HD2 had DRIFTED by inheriting hd1_seq_core first-passage label. CORRECTION: HD2 target = the CONTINUOUS, UNBOUNDED signed forward log-return r_H; metric = rank-IC(pred, r_H) per H (already how eval computed it - the barrier only restricted the eval SUBSET, not the metric target). Economic viability = a SEPARATE annotation (top-decile |move| >= 0.13% cost floor), NOT a cap in the target (HA1 style). The rev5/rev6 barrier round STANDS as an informative detour - findings retained: barrier-width is directional-SKILL-inert (3-seed confirm fp_0.30 +0.0214+-0.0018 ~= fp_0.13 +0.0195+-0.0026); the breakeven economics p*=(1+c/f)/2 (92%@0.13 .. 68%@0.30); SOL weak at every form. R2 (rev7) RE-SCOPED to the continuous target: same loss family (R0/R1/R2_econ/focal/asym/label_smooth/IC) on the unbounded r_H, eval rank-IC vs r_H, select by seed-stable mean rank-IC + econ-annotation. rev1-7 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-23T16:59:16Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev9 R2 LOSS-round result + selection-criterion correction (user 2026-05-24): rank losses by cap_edge_gross (captured signed alpha = magnitude x direction, the user's objective), NOT rank-IC; rank-IC demoted to direction-skill diagnostic; 0.13% cost = separate annotation, not the HD2 metric. Surface argmax = IC (+0.021%/trade captured signed alpha); magnitude-aware losses (IC/asym/R2_econ/R1) > blind (focal/R0/label_smooth). Binding axis for captured alpha = direction skill on large moves, not the loss. Confirm IC vs R1 x3 seeds spawned (native best-val cap_edge).", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 9, "statement": "HD2 rev9 - OBJECTIVE round 2 (LOSS/WEIGHTING) RESULT + SELECTION-CRITERION CORRECTION (user 2026-05-24; exploratory surface, CLAUDE.md). SELECTION CRITERION CORRECTED: rev7 ranked losses by mean rank-IC; CORRECTED to mean cap_edge_gross = the SIGNED captured forward log-return in the top-confidence decile (dir-call sign(logit-median) x r_H, averaged over the top-10pct most-confident OOS points) = the magnitude-AND-direction-scaled alpha the model actually harvests (user objective: bigger correctly-called move -> proportionally bigger reward; wrong on a big move -> bigger penalty). rank-IC is rank-only (magnitude-blind) and DEMOTED to a secondary direction-skill diagnostic. The 0.13pct cost floor = a SEPARATE economic annotation (cap_edge_net), NOT the HD2 metric (frozen contract; HD2 = MAX captured alpha, not a deploy-gate). ALPHA SURFACE (continuous r_H, seed0, L=216000, mean cap_edge_gross %/trade over 6 (sym,H) cells): IC +0.0210 (ARGMAX) > asym +0.0168 > R2_econ +0.0159 > R1 +0.0147 > focal +0.0144 > R0 +0.0110 > label_smooth +0.0062. The four magnitude-aware losses (IC/asym/R2_econ/R1) ALL capture more signed alpha than the three magnitude-blind ones (focal/R0/label_smooth) -> putting move-magnitude into the loss measurably RAISES captured alpha. ARGMAX = IC (directly maximizes corr(sigmoid(logit), r_H) = purest magnitude x direction objective; this IS the user's reward idea). CONDITIONAL STRUCTURE: Mamba-2 is confident on large moves (top-decile |move| ~0.22-0.245pct) but its DIRECTION call on them is near-random (auc ~0.508), so captured signed alpha (~0.006-0.021pct) is an order of magnitude below the unsigned available move -> the BINDING axis for captured alpha is DIRECTION skill on large moves, which the loss modulates only mildly; later rounds (capacity/reg/timescales) or a magnitude-regression head are the candidate levers. [Demoted economic annotation: all losses cap_edge_net < 0 at the 0.13pct floor - NOT the HD2 question.] CAVEAT: the rank-IC criterion (rev7) would have crowned focal; cap_edge crowns IC (focal -> 5th) - the criterion swap materially reorders the field, validating the magnitude-aware selection. Screen seed0 cap_edge was computed via eval-only RESCORE of the saved (last-epoch) ckpts (best_state not separately persisted), so rescore rank-IC drifted vs the original best-val numbers for some losses (R1 .007->.022, asym .005->.024); the CONFIRM recomputes cap_edge NATIVELY on the best-val model. CONFIRM PRE-REG (spawned, 12 units, virginship05 L4): {IC, R1} x {SOL, LTC} x seeds {0,1,2}, fresh training, native best-val cap_edge_gross; FREEZE IC as the HD2 objective IF its mean cap_edge_gross lead over R1 exceeds seed-sd, else keep R1 (incumbent). INFRA: virgin-ship03 hit its billing-cycle spend cap (~30 USD); migrated to virginship05 (Volume re-hydrated from HF streams + salvaged midts; midts also uploaded to HF for portability); all R2 work uses .spawn()+--detach (preemption-robust). rev1-8 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-24T07:55:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev10 R2 CONFIRM+FREEZE: IC beats R1 on cap_edge_gross +0.0230 vs +0.0082 %/trade (delta +0.0148 = 3.4x pooled seed-sd) AND is ~9x more seed-stable. FROZEN HD2 objective = IC loss (corr(sigmoid(logit), r_H) = user's magnitude x direction captured-alpha reward). Binding lever now = direction skill on large moves, not the loss. Next: round 3 (reg) or pivot to a skill/regression lever.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 10, "statement": "HD2 rev10 - OBJECTIVE round 2 (LOSS/WEIGHTING) CONFIRM + FREEZE (exploratory surface, CLAUDE.md). 3-seed confirm: {IC, R1} x {SOL, LTC} x seeds{0,1,2}, fresh training, NATIVE best-val cap_edge_gross (= captured SIGNED alpha = mean over top-confidence decile of sign(logit-median)*r_H = the magnitude x direction reward, user 2026-05-24). SURFACE (mean cap_edge_gross %/trade over the 6 (sym,H) cells, per seed): IC = +0.0224 / +0.0224 / +0.0243 -> mean +0.0230, sd 0.0009. R1 = +0.0055 / +0.0001 / +0.0190 -> mean +0.0082, sd 0.0079. IC lead over incumbent R1 = +0.0148 %/trade ~= 3.4x the pooled seed-sd (0.0044) -> IC beats R1 BEYOND seed noise. IC is ALSO ~9x more seed-STABLE (R1 swings 25x across seeds, 0.0001..0.0190; IC essentially flat). rank-IC diagnostic concurs (IC ~0.0213-0.0230 stable; R1 0.0127-0.0227 noisy). DECISION: FREEZE the HD2 objective = IC loss = maximize corr(sigmoid(logit), r_H) (purest magnitude x direction captured-alpha reward; = the user's stated objective). Frozen IC is carried forward into rounds 3-9. The native best-val confirm SHARPENED the last-epoch rescore (R1 seed0 .0147 -> .0055), strengthening IC's robustness. [Demoted economic annotation, NOT the HD2 metric: captured gross alpha (~0.023%/trade) is still below the 0.13% round-trip cost; HD2 = MAX captured alpha (exploratory), not a deploy-gate. The binding lever for captured alpha is DIRECTION skill on LARGE moves (model confident on ~0.23% moves but auc~0.508 on their direction), a target for later capacity/reg/timescale rounds or a magnitude-REGRESSION head.] rev1-9 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-24T08:40:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev11 ROUND 3 (regularization) PRE-REG: sweep dropout{0.0,0.1,0.2} x wd{1e-4,1e-3,1e-2} (9 combos), IC objective frozen (rev10), target r_H, select by mean cap_edge_gross over 6 (sym,H) cells; screen seed0 x {SOL,LTC} -> confirm winner vs current default (0.1,1e-3) on 3 seeds -> freeze if beats default beyond seed-sd.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 11, "statement": "HD2 rev11 - ROUND 3 (REGULARIZATION: dropout x weight-decay) PRE-REG (FROZEN spec; greedy chain; exploratory surface). PRIORS FROZEN: target = continuous unbounded r_H; OBJECTIVE = IC loss (maximize corr(sigmoid(logit), r_H), frozen rev10); L = 216000; d_model=256, d_state=128, n_layers=4, d_conv=4, expand=2; STRIDE=1; SYMS={SOL-USDT-PERP, LTC-USDT-PERP}; selection metric = mean cap_edge_gross over the 6 (sym,H) cells (rev9; rank-IC = secondary diagnostic; 0.13pct cost = separate annotation, NOT the HD2 metric). SWEEP: dropout x wd grid = {0.0, 0.1, 0.2} x {1e-4, 1e-3, 1e-2} (9 combos; the current default 0.1/1e-3 is an included grid point). SCREEN: 9 combos x {SOL,LTC} x seed0, 10 epochs, L4, .spawn()+--detach (preemption-robust) -> Volume /cache/results/hd2_r3/*.json. RANK by mean cap_edge_gross; CONFIRM the argmax (dropout,wd) vs the current default (0.1,1e-3) on seeds {0,1,2}; FREEZE the winning (dropout,wd) IF its mean cap_edge_gross beats the default beyond seed-sd, else KEEP the default. PRIOR (HD1): regularization is decisive (light->overfit, heavy->underfit plateau, middle open). RATIONALE: R2 (rev9/10) showed the binding lever for captured alpha is DIRECTION skill on large moves (model confident on ~0.23pct moves but auc~0.508 on their direction), not the loss; reg is the next cheap skill/generalization lever in the greedy ladder (user choice 2026-05-24). rev1-10 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-24T08:55:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev12 R3 reg result: surface SHALLOW (cap_gross 0.0179-0.0228 %/trade), argmax = LEAST reg (dropout0/wd1e-4, +0.0228) but within seed-sd of default (0.1/1e-3, +0.0220) -> KEEP DEFAULT (provisional; reg re-pass at full data scale). Signal: more reg HURTS -> model is data-limited at 500d, not overfitting -> data is the lever, not reg.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 12, "statement": "HD2 rev12 - ROUND 3 (REGULARIZATION: dropout x weight-decay) RESULT (exploratory surface; PROVISIONAL at 500d, data-dependent axis). Screen: dropout{0.0,0.1,0.2} x wd{1e-4,1e-3,1e-2} x {SOL,LTC} x seed0, IC objective frozen (rev10), target r_H, L=216000. SURFACE (mean cap_edge_gross %/trade over the 6 (sym,H) cells): argmax (dropout=0.0, wd=1e-4) +0.0228; (0.0,1e-3) +0.0227; DEFAULT (0.1,1e-3) +0.0220; (0.2,1e-4) +0.0218; (0.2,1e-3) +0.0215; (0.1,1e-4) +0.0214; (0.2,1e-2) +0.0202; (0.0,1e-2) +0.0202; (0.1,1e-2) +0.0179. The surface is SHALLOW: full range 0.0179-0.0228 (~0.005%/trade); the top cluster (argmax .0228 down to default .0220) spans ~0.0008% = within the IC seed-sd (~0.0009%, rev10). DECISION (per rev11 pre-reg rule): argmax-minus-default = +0.0009% does NOT exceed seed-sd -> KEEP DEFAULT (dropout=0.1, wd=1e-3); no confident reg winner at this scale; 3-seed confirm SKIPPED (within-noise + reg is data-dependent and will be re-passed at the final data scale). INFORMATIVE STRUCTURE (the actual signal): cap_edge DECREASES monotonic-ish with MORE regularization (worst cells are the wd=1e-2 column; argmax is the LEAST-regularized corner dropout=0/wd=1e-4) -> at 500d the model is NOT overfitting, it is data-limited / underfitting -> regularization is not the binding lever; MORE DATA is indicated. This corroborates rev9/10 (binding lever = direction skill on large moves) and the parallel data-scaling hypothesis (free L1 + all symbols). reg re-pass deferred to the final data scale. rev1-11 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-24T19:45:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev13 ROUND 4 (SSM timescales) PRE-REG: sweep (dt_min,dt_max){slow(1e-4,1e-2)/default(1e-3,1e-1)/fast(1e-2,1.0)} x A_init_range{long(1,4)/default(1,16)/short(1,64) memory} = 9 combos, IC + default-reg frozen, target r_H, select by mean cap_edge_gross, full 500d x 2sym (data-insensitive axis), H100. screen seed0 -> confirm argmax vs default on 3 seeds -> freeze if beats default beyond seed-sd.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 13, "statement": "HD2 rev13 - ROUND 4 (SSM TIMESCALES: dt range x A_init range) PRE-REG (FROZEN spec; greedy chain; exploratory surface, CLAUDE.md). PRIORS FROZEN: target = continuous r_H; OBJECTIVE = IC (rev10); REG = default dropout=0.1/wd=1e-3 (rev12 kept - surface flat at 500d); L=216000; d_model=256, d_state=128, n_layers=4, d_conv=4, expand=2; STRIDE=1; SYMS={SOL,LTC}; selection metric = mean cap_edge_gross over the 6 (sym,H) cells (rank-IC secondary diagnostic; 0.13pct cost = separate annotation, NOT the HD2 metric). SWEEP: (dt_min,dt_max) in {(1e-4,1e-2)=slow, (1e-3,1e-1)=DEFAULT, (1e-2,1.0)=fast} x A_init_range in {(1,4)=long-memory, (1,16)=DEFAULT, (1,64)=short-memory} = 9 combos (these set the SSM's representable time-constants and state-decay = the temporal inductive bias of the mamba kernel). SCREEN: 9 combos x {SOL,LTC} x seed0, 10 epochs, H100, .spawn()+--detach -> /cache/results/hd2_r4. RANK by mean cap_edge_gross; CONFIRM the argmax (dt,A) vs the default (1e-3,1e-1)x(1,16) on seeds {0,1,2}; FREEZE the winning (dt,A) IF its mean cap_edge_gross beats the default beyond seed-sd, else KEEP the default. RATIONALE: timescales are a DATA-INSENSITIVE axis (optimum set by the signal's autocorrelation/temporal structure, not by sample count N) -> the 500d optimum transfers to the larger-data model (data-scaling hypothesis run in a parallel session); screened on the FULL 500d x 2sym (a 50d/1sym subset was rejected by the user as too small for valid research). HW NOTE (science/speed objective, not budget; spare accounts virginship05 active, virginship06 in reserve): H100 for per-unit speed (~3.7x faster wall-clock/unit than L4 in the bench); a util probe showed H100 sits at ~9-10pct utilization on this workload (small model + long L=216000 sequential SSM scan + mostly-solo periods, since many days < 216000 ticks) and CANNOT be saturated by larger batch, so batch_periods=default(2); the real speed lever is parallelism (1 wave per screen). rev1-12 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-24T20:30:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev14 R4 timescales result: seed0 screen suggested slow-dt (+0.0024 over default) but 3-seed confirm DISSOLVED it (slow +0.0220+-0.0003 vs default +0.0217+-0.0012, delta +0.0002 << seed-sd 0.0008) -> KEEP DEFAULT (dt 1e-3..1e-1, A(1,16)). META: rounds 3 (reg) + 4 (timescales) both within-noise flat -> captured alpha robust to architecture HPs on 500d; binding constraint = DATA/direction-skill. Defer capacity rounds (d_state/n_layers/d_model) to scaled data.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 14, "statement": "HD2 rev14 - ROUND 4 (SSM TIMESCALES: dt range x A_init) RESULT + DECISION (exploratory surface, CLAUDE.md). SCREEN (seed0, 500d, 17/18 cells; 1 cell [dt-fast(1e-2,1.0), A(1,16), SOL] lost to Modal preemption mid-final-eval, a non-contender mid-pack combo): mean cap_edge_gross argmax at SLOW dt (1e-4,1e-2) x A(1,16) = +0.0228 vs the mamba DEFAULT (1e-3,1e-1) x A(1,16) = +0.0204 (delta +0.0024 ~ 2.7x seed-sd at seed0); trend slower-dt > default > faster-dt, suggesting the default mamba dt (tuned for short/language sequences) might be too fast for the L=216000 ultra-long financial sequence. CONFIRM (3 seeds {0,1,2} x {SOL,LTC}, fresh, native best-val cap_edge, H100 on virginship06): SLOW-dt = +0.0220 +-0.0003 (seeds .0215/.0223/.0221) vs DEFAULT = +0.0217 +-0.0012 (seeds .0204/.0233/.0215); delta = +0.0002 << pooled seed-sd 0.0008 -> the seed0 advantage DISSOLVED across seeds (default's seed0 0.0204 was a low draw; its seed1 0.0233 exceeds slow-dt). DECISION (per rev13 rule): slow-dt does NOT beat default beyond seed-sd -> KEEP DEFAULT timescales (dt_min=1e-3, dt_max=1e-1, A_init_range=(1,16)). [Aside: slow-dt is ~4x more seed-STABLE (sd .0003 vs .0012) - a minor reliability plus, not a freeze trigger under the cap_edge_gross rule.] META-PATTERN (the actual signal): rounds 3 (REG, rev12) AND 4 (TIMESCALES) both return within-seed-noise-FLAT cap_edge surfaces (all ~+0.020-0.023%/trade) -> Mamba-2's captured alpha on the 500d data is ROBUST / insensitive to these architecture hyperparameters; the binding constraint is DATA / direction-skill on large moves (rev12 'data-limited' finding), NOT architecture tuning. IMPLICATION: the remaining capacity rounds (d_state / n_layers / d_model) - also architecture HPs - are likely flat on 500d as well and are best DEFERRED to the scaled-data regime (the parallel data-hypothesis session: free L1 + all symbols). INFRA: virginship05 exhausted on R4 (18 H100 units), migrated to virginship06 (LAST spare account; Volume re-hydrated from HF streams + local midts); rounds-4 compute on H100 for per-unit speed (~9pct util inherent at L=216000, science/speed objective). rev1-13 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-24T21:20:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev15 ROUND 4b (d_conv local conv width) PRE-REG: sweep d_conv in {2,3,4} (causal_conv1d-supported) x {SOL,LTC} x seed0, IC+default reg+default timescales frozen, select by mean cap_edge_gross. SCREEN-ONLY (cheap, ~6 H100 units) -> confirm only if a clear winner beyond seed-sd. Last data-insensitive axis; capacity rounds deferred to scaled data. virginship06 (last account).", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 15, "statement": "HD2 rev15 - ROUND 4b (d_conv: local causal-conv width) PRE-REG (FROZEN; greedy chain; exploratory surface). PRIORS FROZEN: target r_H; objective IC (rev10); reg default dropout=0.1/wd=1e-3 (rev12); timescales default dt(1e-3,1e-1)/A(1,16) (rev14); L=216000; d_model=256, d_state=128, n_layers=4, expand=2; STRIDE=1; SYMS={SOL,LTC}; selection = mean cap_edge_gross over 6 (sym,H) cells. SWEEP: d_conv in {2, 3, 4} (the local depthwise causal-conv kernel width in Mamba2; controls short-range temporal mixing of the LOB stream; causal_conv1d kernel supports widths 2/3/4; 4 = mamba default). SCREEN-ONLY: 3 widths x {SOL,LTC} x seed0, 10 epochs, H100, .spawn()+--detach -> /cache/results/hd2_r4b. Rank by mean cap_edge_gross; run a 3-seed CONFIRM ONLY IF a width beats default(4) by more than the ~0.001 seed-sd (user choice 2026-05-24: cheap screen, conserve the last account). RATIONALE: d_conv is a DATA-INSENSITIVE axis (local temporal structure) -> 500d optimum transfers; it is the LAST data-insensitive architecture knob. Capacity axes (d_state/n_layers/d_model) are DEFERRED to the scaled-data regime (parallel data-hypothesis session), per the rev12+rev14 meta-finding that captured alpha is flat to architecture HPs on 500d (data-limited). INFRA: virginship06 (LAST spare account; 03+05 exhausted), H100. rev1-14 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-24T21:40:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev16 R4b d_conv result: surface shallow, weak consistent trend smaller-better (d_conv=3 +0.0233 argmax & d_conv=2 +0.0228 both > default 4 +0.0219; +0.0014 ~1.4x seed-sd = marginal, NOT clear) -> KEEP DEFAULT d_conv=4, no confirm (rev14 precedent: such deltas dissolve; conserve last account 06). COMPLETES data-insensitive architecture axes (loss=IC / reg=def / timescales=def / d_conv=def). Capacity axes -> scaled data (parallel agent). 500d HD2 architecture sweep complete.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 16, "statement": "HD2 rev16 - ROUND 4b (d_conv: local causal-conv width) RESULT + DECISION (exploratory surface, CLAUDE.md). SCREEN (seed0, 500d, d_conv in {2,3,4} x {SOL,LTC}; causal_conv1d supports widths 2/3/4, no kernel issue): mean cap_edge_gross d_conv=3 = +0.0233 (argmax), d_conv=2 = +0.0228, d_conv=4 (DEFAULT) = +0.0219. Weak but CONSISTENT trend: SMALLER d_conv (2,3) > default (4) on BOTH cap_edge_gross AND rank_ic (d_conv 2&3 rank_ic 0.0229 vs d_conv 4: 0.0220) -> slightly tighter local conv may help the LOB short-range mixing. HOWEVER the argmax delta (d_conv=3 minus default = +0.0014) is only ~1.4x seed-sd (~0.001) = MARGINAL, not a clear winner; the rev14 precedent showed a larger seed0 delta (2.7x seed-sd) DISSOLVE under a 3-seed confirm. DECISION (per rev15 rule 'confirm only if clear winner beyond seed-sd' + conserve the LAST spare account virginship06): NOT clear enough -> KEEP DEFAULT d_conv=4; no 3-seed confirm spent. MILESTONE: this COMPLETES the data-INSENSITIVE architecture axes on 500d -> objective=IC (frozen rev10), reg=default 0.1/1e-3 (rev12), timescales=default dt(1e-3,1e-1)/A(1,16) (rev14), d_conv=default 4 (rev16). META (rev12+rev14+rev16): EVERY architecture-HP surface is within/near seed-noise FLAT on 500d (captured alpha ~+0.020-0.023%/trade everywhere) -> Mamba-2's captured alpha here is DATA-limited, not architecture-limited; the binding constraint is direction-skill on large moves (auc~0.508), which more DATA (not HP tuning) is the lever for. NEXT: the capacity axes (d_state / n_layers / d_model) are DEFERRED to the scaled-data regime (parallel data-hypothesis session: free L1 + all symbols), where added capacity + a reg re-pass become meaningful; the 500d HD2 architecture sweep is COMPLETE. INFRA: 03+05 exhausted, on virginship06 (last spare account). rev1-15 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-24T22:05:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev17 DATA-SCALE axis PRE-REG: 500d architecture flat (rev12/14/16 -> data-limited) => test if MORE DATA lifts captured alpha. Built all 8 Binance-perp symbols full days (4936 symbol-days, 41GB compressed in GCS). POOLED train on all 8 (global temporal split <2025-12-10), EVAL on LTC (>=2025-12-10, no leak). Compare cap_edge_gross(LTC) of all-8-pooled vs LTC-only-pooled. Early 2-ep signal: pooling lifts LTC auc 0.507->0.510. IC + default reg/timescales/d_conv frozen.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 17, "statement": "HD2 rev17 - DATA-SCALE axis PRE-REG (FROZEN spec; exploratory surface, user 2026-05-25). MOTIVATION: the 500d architecture sweep is within-noise FLAT on every axis (loss=IC frozen rev10; reg rev12, timescales rev14, d_conv rev16 all kept-default) -> captured alpha is DATA-limited, binding constraint = direction-skill on large moves (auc~0.508). TEST: does MORE DATA (cross-symbol) lift it? DATASET: all 8 Binance-USDT-PERP symbols with full L2 history (BNB 546, BTC 363, DOGE 545, ETH 362, LINK 788, LTC 1243, SOL 544, XRP 545 = 4936 symbol-days; built on a 96-vCPU GCP VM, np.savez_compressed -> 41GB in gs://.../hd2_cache_v1, hydrated to Modal Volume). The 80-ch stream is SCALE-INVARIANT (prices mid-relative (p-mid)/mid, sizes log1p) so cross-symbol pooling + pooled normalization is valid. METHOD: POOLED multi-symbol training (FullCfg.pooled): train = ALL symbols' days with date < split_date=2025-12-10; EVAL = LTC-USDT-PERP days >= 2025-12-10 (user: validate on LTC; SOL deferred to budget/next account). GLOBAL TEMPORAL split = no leakage (all train days strictly before all eval days; H<<1day, days are independent reset segments). Objective IC + default reg (0.1,1e-3) + default timescales (dt 1e-3..1e-1, A(1,16)) + d_conv 4 FROZEN; L=216000; seed0; 10 epochs; H100. PRIMARY COMPARISON: mean cap_edge_gross (LTC eval, over the 3 H) of {all-8 pooled} vs {LTC-only pooled} (identical split+eval) -> does adding 7 symbols' data lift LTC's captured alpha / direction skill? Pooled n=5.52M dps (train 3.85M, LTC-eval 63k). Early 2-epoch signal: pooling lifts LTC auc 0.507->0.510 and rank_ic comparably (direction skill, the bottleneck) - encouraging, to be confirmed at 10 epochs. Terminal labels derived from cached rH (== labels_for_H log(mid[jH]/m0) == make_target terminal; meta-load 1h44->15min). If pooling lifts LTC cap_edge beyond seed-sd -> data IS the lever -> then re-run capacity axes (d_state/n_layers/d_model) on the pooled data. INFRA: virginship06 active (07 in reserve); H100, memory=96GB (pooled meta). rev1-16 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-25T02:10:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev18 DATA-SCALE result (seed0): pooled all-8 train vs LTC-only train, both eval LTC. cap_edge_gross(LTC) mean: all-8 +0.0110% vs LTC-only +0.0158% -> delta -0.0048% (pooling LOWERED captured alpha; ~beyond IC seed-sd but single seed). rank_ic/auc marginally HIGHER for all-8 (better ordering, worse top-decile harvest). Cross-symbol data did NOT lift LTC captured alpha by cap_edge -> data-limited premise WEAKENED; likely a signal/feature ceiling, not a Mamba-2 config lever. Needs 3-seed confirm. Fork: (a) confirm seeds, (b) d_state on pooled anyway, (c) reconsider.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 18, "statement": "HD2 rev18 - DATA-SCALE result (seed0; exploratory surface, CLAUDE.md). Pooled all-8 train vs LTC-only train (identical global temporal split, both eval LTC >=2025-12-10; IC + default arch; 10 epochs early-stopped). mean cap_edge_gross(LTC): all-8 = +0.0110% (H 0.0032/0.0084/0.0215) vs LTC-only = +0.0158% (H 0.0037/0.0131/0.0306) -> DELTA -0.0048% (all-8 LOWER; ~beyond the tight IC seed-sd ~0.001, but SINGLE SEED). Meanwhile rank_ic and auc were marginally HIGHER for all-8 (rank_ic 0.0207/0.0173/0.0234 vs 0.0189/0.0160/0.0218; auc 0.5106/0.5078/0.5088 vs 0.5102/0.5071/0.5087) -> cross-symbol pooling improved overall ORDERING/direction slightly but the TOP-confidence-decile captured signed return DROPPED (its confident LTC bets harvest less). READING: cross-symbol data scaling did NOT lift LTC captured alpha by the cap_edge criterion (slightly lowered it). This WEAKENS the rev12/14/16 'data-limited' premise. Combined with the within-noise-FLAT 500d architecture surfaces (loss=IC frozen; reg/timescales/d_conv kept-default), the evidence now points toward a SIGNAL/FEATURE ceiling (LOB -> 30min signed-return predictability) rather than a Mamba-2-configuration lever: Mamba-2's max captured alpha on this data sits ~+0.015-0.022%/trade (LTC), robust to architecture AND to cross-symbol data scale, and ~6x below the 0.13% cost floor. CAVEAT: single seed (seed0) on a noisy top-decile metric; a 3-seed confirm is needed before firming this. INFRA: all-8 (pooled n=5.52M, train 3.85M, LTC-eval 63k) on virginship06 H100, preempted + auto-resumed (retries=2, ckpt-resume). rev1-17 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-25T04:35:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev19 FRAMING CORRECTION (user 2026-05-25): HD2 = conditional surface 'under what conditions is Mamba 2 STRONGER', selection by RELATIVE cap_edge_gross. The 0.13% economic barrier is NOT applied at this stage (NOT a deploy-gate) -> disregard rev18's 'ceiling/below-cost' framing. Cross-symbol pooling = ENABLER to have enough data for DATA-DEPENDENT param sweeps (model size etc.), NOT a 'does data help' verdict; the rev18 all-8-vs-LTC-only delta is incidental, not the goal. NEXT: sweep capacity (d_state/n_layers/d_model/expand-headdim) + reg-re-pass on pooled data, eval LTC, select by relative cap_edge_gross.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 19, "statement": "HD2 rev19 - FRAMING CORRECTION (user 2026-05-25; exploratory surface, CLAUDE.md). The HD2 question is purely CONDITIONAL: 'under what conditions (objective, reg, timescales, block-shape, CAPACITY, data scale, ...) is Mamba 2 STRONGER', measured by RELATIVE cap_edge_gross (captured signed alpha = magnitude x direction). CORRECTIONS: (1) the 0.13pct round-trip cost barrier is NOT a criterion at this stage - it is a far-future deploy question, not the tier question; rev18's 'signal/feature ceiling, ~6x below cost' framing is the banned deploy-gate collapse and is RETRACTED. Configs are compared RELATIVELY, not against the cost floor. (2) Cross-symbol pooling (all 8 symbols) was chosen NOT as 'more data is better' but purely as the ENABLER to have enough data to sweep DATA-DEPENDENT Mamba-2 parameters (d_state / n_layers / d_model / expand-headdim, plus a reg re-pass) in a regime where they can express; the rev18 all-8-vs-LTC-only comparison is an incidental substrate check, NOT the deliverable. DELIVERABLE = the RELATIVE cap_edge_gross surface over the capacity axes on pooled data (train all-8, eval LTC). State so far (RELATIVE cap_edge_gross): obj loss IC frozen (+0.0230 vs R1 +0.0082, 3-seed); reg/timescales/d_conv kept-default (within-noise flat on 500d). NEXT: d_state {64,128,256,512} pooled screen (seed0) -> confirm 3 seeds -> freeze by relative cap_edge_gross; then n_layers, expand/headdim, d_model, reg re-pass. rev1-18 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-25T05:05:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev20 PRE-REG (before running): CAPACITY round 1 = d_state {64,128,256,512} sweep on POOLED all-8 (train < split_date 2025-12-10, eval LTC >= 2025-12-10), the first DATA-DEPENDENT axis (rev19 framing: pooling = ENABLER for capacity sweeps). Frozen priors carried in: target r_H (rev8), loss IC (rev10), reg dropout0.1/wd1e-3 (rev12), timescales dt 1e-3..1e-1/A_init(1,16) (rev14), d_conv 4 (rev16), L=216000, d_model=256, n_layers=4, expand=2. SELECT by RELATIVE cap_edge_gross (mean over the 3 H cells on LTC OOS); NO 0.13pct econ gate at this stage (rev19). Method: screen seed0 (4 units, H100, spawn+detach) -> pick argmax relative cap_edge_gross -> confirm winner vs default d_state=128 on 3 seeds -> freeze. Secondary annotations: cap_edge_net, rank_ic, auc. Orchestrator: hd2_objsweep_modal.py --capsweep (round='cap', d_state task override; results -> Volume /cache/results/hd2_cap/CAP_ds{N}_s0.json). rev1-19 UNCHANGED (append-only).", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 20, "statement": "HD2 rev20 - CAPACITY round 1 (d_state), exploratory conditional surface (CLAUDE.md). Question unchanged from rev19: 'under what conditions is Mamba 2 STRONGER', measured by RELATIVE cap_edge_gross (captured signed alpha = magnitude x direction; preds = raw logits; mean over the 3 H cells {180,600,1800}s on the LTC OOS test). This is the FIRST data-dependent (capacity) axis, run on POOLED all-8 data purely as the ENABLER (rev19) for a param that needs data scale to express. SWEEP: d_state in {64, 128, 256, 512} (SSM recurrent state dim = the core memory capacity). FROZEN PRIORS carried in unchanged: target = continuous signed forward log-return r_H (rev8); objective/loss = IC = -corr(sigmoid(logit), r_H) (rev10); reg dropout 0.1 / wd 1e-3 (rev12); timescales dt_min 1e-3 / dt_max 1e-1 / A_init_range (1,16) (rev14); d_conv 4 (rev16); L=216000; STRIDE=1; d_model=256 (kernel constraint); n_layers=4; expand=2. DATA CONTRACT (pooled): train = all 8 symbols (BNB/BTC/DOGE/ETH/LINK/LTC/SOL/XRP) with dt < split_date 2025-12-10; eval = LTC-USDT-PERP with dt >= 2025-12-10; global temporal split (no leakage; days = independent reset segments, H << 1 day); 80-ch LOB scale-invariant so cross-symbol pooling is valid. SELECTION = RELATIVE cap_edge_gross between the 4 d_state configs; the 0.13pct round-trip cost barrier is NOT a criterion at this stage (far-future deploy question, rev19); cap_edge_net / rank_ic / auc are SECONDARY annotations only. METHOD: screen seed0 (4 units on H100, spawn + --detach, idempotent -> poll Volume) -> pick argmax relative cap_edge_gross -> confirm that winner vs default d_state=128 on 3 seeds {0,1,2} -> freeze by relative cap_edge_gross. Then n_layers, expand/headdim, d_model, reg re-pass. rev1-19 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-25T06:30:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev21 (2026-05-25): d_state CAPACITY round 1 RESULT + PROVISIONAL FREEZE. SCREEN (seed0, pooled all-8 train<2025-12-10, eval LTC>=, mean cap_edge_gross over H={180,600,1800}, %/trade): ds64=0.0118, ds128=0.0115, ds256=0.0146 (ARGMAX), ds512=0.0116. Surface = single elevated point at d_state=256; 64/128/512 clustered ~0.0116 (flat). 3-seed confirm (ds256 vs ds128) was launched but virginship06 hit the workspace billing-cycle spend limit mid-run (units stuck at ep1-2, no JSON completion); user (2026-05-25) elected to FREEZE d_state=256 on the seed0 screen and conserve the last reserve account (skip confirm). CAVEAT: the 256 lift (~+0.0030 over the 64/128/512 cluster, ~2.5-3x prior seed-sd) is seed0-ONLY, NOT seed-verified -- prior rounds showed seed0 hints can dissolve on 3 seeds (timescales rev14). Carried forward to n_layers as a provisional prior: d_state=256. NO 0.13% econ gate at this stage (rev19). NEXT: n_layers {2,4,6,8} pooled screen on virginship07 (A100 fallback; H100 scarce+pricey on Modal). rev1-20 UNCHANGED (append-only).", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 21, "statement": "HD2 rev21 - d_state CAPACITY round 1 surface + provisional freeze (exploratory conditional-optimization, CLAUDE.md). SURFACE (the deliverable): RELATIVE cap_edge_gross (captured signed alpha, mean over the 3 H cells {180,600,1800}s on LTC OOS, %/trade), seed0 screen on POOLED all-8 (train < split_date 2025-12-10, eval LTC >=), IC objective + frozen reg/timescales/d_conv priors: d_state=64 -> 0.0118, d_state=128 -> 0.0115, d_state=256 -> 0.0146 (ARGMAX), d_state=512 -> 0.0116. The surface is NON-MONOTONIC with a single elevated point at d_state=256; the other three configs (64/128/512) are clustered flat at ~0.0116. Per-H, captured alpha concentrates at the long horizon H1800 (~0.022%) across all configs. ARGMAX = d_state=256, magnitude of its edge over the cluster ~+0.0030 (~2.5-3x prior seed-sd). DECISION: freeze d_state=256 as the carried-forward prior for subsequent capacity rounds. PROVENANCE / CAVEAT (secondary): this freeze is PROVISIONAL on the seed0 screen only -- the planned 3-seed confirm (ds256 vs default ds128) was launched but virginship06 reached its workspace spend limit before any unit completed (units preempted at ep1-2, no result); the user elected (2026-05-25) to freeze on the screen argmax and conserve the last reserve account rather than re-hydrate + re-run on virginship07. The seed-stability of the 256 lift is therefore UNVERIFIED and could dissolve under more seeds (as the timescales hint did in rev14); revisit with a 3-seed confirm if budget allows. Cost annotation: 0.13% round-trip is NOT a criterion at this stage (rev19); cap_edge_net/rank_ic/auc are secondary. NEXT axis: n_layers {2,4,6,8}, pooled all-8, d_state=256 carried in, screen seed0, on virginship07 (A100 -- Modal H100 capacity scarce/pricey). rev1-20 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-25T22:40:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev22 PRE-REG (before running): CAPACITY round 2 = n_layers (depth) sweep on POOLED all-8 (train < split_date 2025-12-10, eval LTC >=), d_state=256 carried in as the rev21 PROVISIONAL prior. Sweep n_layers {2,6,8}; the n_layers=4 point REUSES the d_state-screen ds256 result (CAP_ds256_s0 = d_state256/n_layers4-default = 0.0146 %/trade) to avoid a redundant run and conserve the LAST reserve account virginship07 (06 exhausted its spend limit). IC objective + frozen reg(0.1/1e-3)/timescales(dt1e-3..1e-1,A1-16)/d_conv4 priors. SELECT by RELATIVE cap_edge_gross (mean over 3 H cells {180,600,1800} on LTC OOS); NO 0.13pct econ gate (rev19). Method: screen seed0 (3 A100 units; H100 scarce/pricey on Modal; GPU is selection-invariant per bench) -> confirm only if budget allows. Orchestrator: hd2_objsweep_modal.py --nlsweep (round='cap', n_layers+d_state task overrides, tag CAP_ds256_nl{N}_s0, sub hd2_cap). Data re-hydrated streams-only to virginship07 Volume (terminal fast-path: midts not needed). rev1-21 UNCHANGED (append-only).", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 22, "statement": "HD2 rev22 - CAPACITY round 2 (n_layers / depth), exploratory conditional surface (CLAUDE.md). Question unchanged: 'under what conditions is Mamba 2 STRONGER', measured by RELATIVE cap_edge_gross (captured signed alpha = magnitude x direction; mean over the 3 H cells {180,600,1800}s on the LTC OOS test, %/trade). SWEEP: n_layers in {2, 4, 6, 8} (model depth), where the n_layers=4 cell is taken from the d_state-screen ds256 result (CAP_ds256_s0 = 0.0146; d_state=256, n_layers=4-default) and {2,6,8} are run fresh -> 3 new units. CARRIED-IN PRIORS (frozen): d_state=256 (rev21, PROVISIONAL -- seed0-only, confirm skipped for budget); target = continuous r_H (rev8); loss = IC (rev10); reg dropout0.1/wd1e-3 (rev12); timescales dt1e-3..1e-1/A(1,16) (rev14); d_conv4 (rev16); L=216000; d_model=256; expand=2. DATA CONTRACT (pooled): train = all 8 symbols dt < 2025-12-10; eval = LTC dt >= 2025-12-10; global temporal split (no leakage); 80-ch LOB scale-invariant. SELECTION = RELATIVE cap_edge_gross across the n_layers configs; the 0.13pct cost barrier is NOT a criterion (rev19); cap_edge_net/rank_ic/auc are secondary. METHOD: screen seed0 on A100 (Modal H100 capacity scarce + pricey; GPU choice is selection-invariant per the bench round), spawn + --detach, idempotent -> poll Volume; pick argmax relative cap_edge_gross; 3-seed confirm only if the last account (virginship07) has budget. INFRA NOTE: virginship06 reached its workspace spend limit on the d_state round; switched to virginship07 (LAST reserve) + re-hydrated streams-only; after 07 is exhausted, ask the user. rev1-21 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-25T23:35:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev23 RESULTS-MAP (navesti poryadok, user 2026-05-26): consolidates WHERE all HD2/Mamba-2 results live so they are findable from the committed ledger (another agent could not locate them); + records the user framing correction. No new files; rigorous per-experiment back-fill into experiments.jsonl deferred to a separate session. rev1-22 UNCHANGED (append-only).", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 23, "statement": "HD2 rev23 - Mamba-2 RESULTS MAP + framing correction (user 2026-05-26). PURPOSE: make all HD2 results locatable from the committed ledger. WHERE RESULTS LIVE: (A) Canonical numbers = hypotheses.jsonl HD2 revisions (this file): rev1 L-context sweep; rev9+rev10 objective/loss (IC frozen); rev12 reg; rev14 timescales; rev16 d_conv; rev17/18 data-scale pooling; rev20 d_state pre-reg; rev21 d_state result+freeze; rev22 n_layers pre-reg. (B) experiments.jsonl currently has ONLY the rev1 L-sweep as structured rows (6: LTC/SOL x H180/600/1800, ids hd2-20260523_*); the loss/reg/timescales/d_conv/data-scale/d_state rounds are NOT yet structured rows there (they exist only as rev prose here) -- that gap is why they were not found; structured back-fill = separate session (needs n_eff/provenance not computed for the capacity screens, do NOT fabricate). (C) Raw per-run JSON on Modal Volume hd2-cache at /cache/results/, ACCOUNT-SCOPED + scattered: hd2_obj, hd2_r2 and hd2_r2_confirm, hd2_r3, hd2_r4 and hd2_r4_confirm, hd2_r4b -> virginship05 (EXHAUSTED); hd2_cap (d_state) + hd2_cap_confirm -> virginship06 (EXHAUSTED, spend-limit); n_layers (hd2_cap CAP_ds256_nl2/6/8) -> virginship07 (ACTIVE). Local untracked mirrors: _tmp_r2*, _tmp_r3, hd2res, hd2obj. SURFACE (RELATIVE cap_edge_gross, pct/trade, the selection metric): loss IC +0.0230 3-seed (vs R1 +0.0082); reg dropout-x-wd flat 0.018-0.023 (kept default 0.1/1e-3); timescales flat (kept default); d_conv flat (kept 4); data-scale pooled all-8 +0.0110 vs LTC-only +0.0158 (seed0, eval LTC); d_state seed0 screen 64=0.0118 / 128=0.0115 / 256=0.0146 (argmax) / 512=0.0116 -> freeze d_state=256 PROVISIONAL (3-seed confirm skipped, 06 spend-limit). FRAMING CORRECTION (user, supersedes my earlier '0.51 wall'): the ~0.51 directional AUC is the ALL-SAMPLE AVERAGE, NOT the project ceiling -- TCN/Mamba-2/XGBoost reach higher. The real lever is SELECTIVITY: model confidence and win-rate correlate near-linearly (~45 deg), so trading only the highest-confidence signals lifts WR to ~70 pct at R:R 1:1 (achieved historically; that data was LOST with the Tokyo server -- only partial RESEARCH_LOG execution characteristics survived, a fraction of millions of configs). cap_edge_gross (signed capture in the top-confidence decile) IS exactly this selectivity metric, so HD2 measures the right thing; the '0.51 ceiling/wall' phrasing is RETRACTED. rev1-22 UNCHANGED. STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-26T00:40:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HDX", "rev": 1, "status": "active", "ts": "2026-05-26T02:00:00Z", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "note": "Created 2026-05-26 per user as the XGBoost analog of HD1(TCN)/HD2(Mamba-2): map XGBoost's conditional alpha surface. Objective + success-metric matched 1:1 to HD2 (continuous r_H target, IC loss, cap_edge_gross headline, no 0.13 barrier; refs HD2 rev8/10/17/19) for a direct XGB-vs-Mamba2 comparison. FROZEN pre-reg; H-SWEEP NOT STARTED per user (awaiting explicit go). Appended to the working ledger WITHOUT commit (parallel agent's HD2 rev3-23 + scripts are uncommitted here; joint commit deferred to the branch owner).", "statement": "HDX rev1 - XGBoost conditional alpha-surface tier, FROZEN PRE-REG (exploratory conditional-optimization, CLAUDE.md; surface-not-verdict, sec5 secondary). QUESTION: under what conditions is XGBoost STRONGER, measured by RELATIVE cap_edge_gross (captured signed alpha = magnitude x direction). MATCHED 1:1 TO HD2 (Mamba-2) for direct comparison: TARGET = continuous unbounded signed forward log-return r_H (NOT first-passage barrier; HD2 rev8); OBJECTIVE = IC loss = maximize corr(pred, r_H) (HD2 rev10) -- XGB realization = custom IC objective (grad of -Pearson(pred,r_H)); documented fallback reg:squarederror on r_H if custom obj unstable; HEADLINE METRIC = cap_edge_gross = mean over the top-confidence decile (by |pred|) of sign(pred)*r_H, %/trade (HD2 rev10), compared RELATIVELY across configs; the 0.13pct round-trip cost is NOT a criterion at this stage (HD2 rev19) -- cap_edge_net / rank_ic / auc are SECONDARY annotations only. DATA CONTRACT (matched to HD2 rev17): features_v1 (59-col engineered features = XGB input analog of HD2's 80-ch raw L2 stream), all 8 Cryptolake Binance-USDT-PERP symbols; POOLED train = all-8 symbol-days dt < split_date 2025-12-10; EVAL = LTC-USDT-PERP days >= 2025-12-10; GLOBAL temporal split (no leakage); per-symbol train-fit normalization. FIRST CELL (agreed, user 2026-05-26): step1 = fix objective=IC (match Mamba-2); step2 = sweep HORIZON H in {180,600,1800}s (+3600 candidate) -> argmax cap_edge_gross + seed-stability (multi-seed). ANCHOR: HD2 Mamba-2 frozen-IC cap_edge_gross = +0.0230 pct/trade (3-seed), captured alpha concentrates at H1800. AXES DEFERRED to later cells: feature-set composition (L2-micro/xs/orth/events), objective family, pooling/scope, depth/eta/reg. STATUS: FROZEN pre-reg; H-SWEEP NOT STARTED per user 2026-05-26 (awaiting go). Mechanics: registered in live ledger; harness to be built; smoke (LTC+1) -> pooled-8 ONLY on user go."}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev24 COURSE-CORRECTION (user 2026-05-26): capacity-UP axis CLOSED as a dead end. Diagnosis: params (5-30M for d_model256 x n_layers up-to-8 x d_state up-to-512) >> EFFECTIVE independent samples. Effective n is tiny: measured n_eff/n_samples = 1-7% (rev1: LTC H180 5.6%, H600 3.1%, H1800 1.5%; SOL 7.2/2.3/1.0%) due to STRIDE=1 decision-point autocorrelation + overlapping forward windows + 3-H multitask redundancy. Nominal train ~3.08M DP/epoch (fit=80% of n_tr 3.85M) but effective ~tens-of-k. Empirical confirmation: epoch curves show train_loss decreasing monotonically while val_ricsum peaks at ep0-2 then degrades on ALL depths -> fast overfit; early-stop carries the load. n_layers surface plateaus (nl2 0.0114 < nl4 0.0146 ~ nl6 0.0142; nl8 abandoned at ep4, budget). DECISIONS: keep n_layers=4 (default, plateau top); d_state=256 provisional freeze (rev21) DEMOTED (capacity not the lever); DROP expand/headdim & d_model-up sweeps. Trainer now persists epoch_hist (learning curve) in result-JSON. PIVOT: lever = EFFECTIVE samples + regularization, NOT capacity. Next axes: (1) STRIDE / decision-point de-correlation (fewer independent train samples vs dense autocorrelated), (2) reg re-pass at scale; likely on LTC-only (rev18: LTC-only +0.0158 > pooled all-8 +0.0110 -> pooling diluted LTC, consistent). rev1-23 UNCHANGED.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 24, "statement": "HD2 rev24 - COURSE-CORRECTION: the capacity-UP sweep axis is closed (exploratory result, CLAUDE.md). SURFACE/finding: across d_state {64,128,256,512} (rev21, seed0: 0.0118/0.0115/0.0146/0.0116) and n_layers {2,4,6,8} (rev22: nl2 0.0114, nl4 0.0146, nl6 0.0142, nl8 abandoned@ep4) the RELATIVE cap_edge_gross surface is flat-to-plateaued (argmax small, ~1-3x seed-sd, single seed). MECHANISM (the actual deliverable here): the model is EFFECTIVE-data-limited, not capacity-limited. Effective independent samples = n_eff/n_samples ~1-7% (measured rev1) because decision points are densely sampled (STRIDE=1) with heavily overlapping H=180-1800s forward windows and near-identical LOB context, plus 3-H multitask shares one context. So nominal ~3.08M train DP/epoch deflate to ~tens-of-thousands effectively independent, weakly-labeled (~0.51 all-sample AUC) points, against 5-30M params -> the model saturates the independent information in 0-2 epochs then memorizes (epoch_hist: train loss monotone down, val_ricsum peaks ep0-2 then declines; early-stop restores the peak). Adding parameters cannot add alpha in this regime, only overfit faster + cost more (~1.5h/epoch pooled). DECISIONS: n_layers frozen at 4 (default; plateau top, beyond-4 adds no alpha); d_state=256 (rev21 provisional) DEMOTED -- capacity is not the lever; expand/headdim and d_model-up sweeps DROPPED. PIVOT (new levers, opposite of capacity-up): (1) EFFECTIVE-sample axis -- STRIDE / decision-point de-correlation (train on more-independent points; tests whether 'more data' becomes 'more information'); (2) regularization re-pass at scale (control the fast overfit); to be run on LTC-only (faster + rev18 showed LTC-only +0.0158 > pooled all-8 +0.0110, i.e. pooling diluted rather than helped -- consistent with the effective-sample lens). Frozen contract (target r_H, loss IC, reg/timescales/d_conv, L=216000, d_model=256) UNCHANGED. rev1-23 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-26T04:30:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HDX", "rev": 2, "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-26T03:30:00Z", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": "hdx-20260526_xgb_snapshot_Hsweep", "note": "rev2 FIRST-CELL RESULT (cache built by optimized Rust hd1_seq_build, cargo 24s, 3606 sym-days, ~17min total VM). cap_edge_gross surface: IC objective monotone-rises with H (0.0048->0.0056->0.0098 at H180/300/600, seed-stable sd~0.001), argmax H600; sq noisier/non-monotone. IC>sq (mirrors HD2 rev10). XGB last-tick snapshot ~2-4x below Mamba-2 L-history stream (+0.0230) -> temporal context is the differentiator. Uncommitted append (parallel-agent WIP). json gs://.../research_runs/hdx/hdx_xgb.json.", "statement": "HDX rev2 - FIRST-CELL RESULT: XGBoost cap_edge_gross H-sweep on the 46-feat decision-tick SNAPSHOT, matched 1:1 to HD2 (continuous r_H labels via Rust hd1_seq_build, bit-exact; pooled all-8 train days<2025-12-10 n=809782, eval LTC>=split n=15812, window>=2024-12-25; cap_edge_gross = mean top-confidence-decile sign(pred)*r_H %/trade; objectives sq=reg:squarederror + custom IC; 3 seeds). PRIMARY SURFACE (cap_edge_gross %/trade, mean+-seed_sd): IC objective = +0.0048+-0.0010 (H180), +0.0056+-0.0011 (H300), +0.0098+-0.0010 (H600) -- MONOTONE-RISING with H, seed-stable; argmax = H600 (longest tested). sq objective = +0.0030 (H180), +0.0081 (H300), -0.0043+-0.006 (H600) -- noisier, non-monotone, negative+unstable at H600. IC dominates sq at H180 and H600 and is ~6x more seed-stable at H600 -> for XGBoost the IC objective is the better-conditioned choice (mirrors HD2 rev10 IC>R1). rank_IC concurs (IC 0.0152/0.0141/0.0092 vs sq 0.0034/0.0050/0.0080). med|move| rises 0.057->0.076->0.113% with H. SECONDARY (deploy-distance, not headline; HD2 rev19): captured alpha ~0.005-0.010 %/trade sits below the 0.13% cost floor -- cost NOT a criterion at this surface stage. SECONDARY (cross-model, identical labels/grid/eval-LTC): XGB on the last-tick SNAPSHOT reaches ~2-4x BELOW Mamba-2's L-history STREAM cap_edge (+0.0230, HD2 rev10) -> the temporal L-context the snapshot lacks is the differentiator (the sequence model's contribution), consistent with HD2's long-context result. NEXT: extend H to 1800 (captured alpha projected to peak given the monotone rise) via a lean rH-builder; then objective-family / feature-set / selectivity axes (HDX_LEVERS A-E). rev1 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing."}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev25 PRE-REG: reg re-pass (dropout x wd) at scale on the overfit regime. Frozen from capacity work: n_layers=4 (rev22 best depth: nl4 0.0146 argmax ~ nl6 0.0142 > nl2 0.0114), d_state=128 (256 demoted rev24). Motivation: epoch_hist shows fast overfit (val_ricsum peaks ep0-2, train loss monotone down) -> rev12's reg sweep (500d single-symbol, grid dropout {0,0.1,0.2}) found LESS reg better (underfit read), but on the full-history overfit regime STRONGER reg may help. Grid: dropout {0.1(base),0.3,0.5} x wd {1e-3,1e-2} (4 cells: (0.1,1e-3),(0.3,1e-3),(0.5,1e-3),(0.3,1e-2)). Substrate LTC-only (rev18: +0.0158 > pooled +0.0110; ~8x cheaper than pooled), STRIDE1 full days (accuracy; stride5 day-stride showed -25% cap_edge so stride confounds reg). IC, terminal, L=216000, eval full LTC >= split. SELECT by RELATIVE cap_edge_gross vs baseline (0.1,1e-3)~+0.0158. screen seed0 -> confirm winner if it beats baseline > seed-sd. Orchestrator --regpass (round='pool', dropout/wd overrides, tag POOL_reg_d{D}_wd{W}_s0) on train_big. rev1-24 UNCHANGED.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 25, "statement": "HD2 rev25 - regularization re-pass (dropout x wd), exploratory conditional surface (CLAUDE.md). Question: does stronger regularization raise RELATIVE cap_edge_gross by controlling the fast overfit now visible in epoch_hist (val_ricsum peaks at ep0-2 then degrades on all configs; train loss falls monotonically). CARRIED-IN (from the closed capacity work): n_layers=4 (rev22 best depth), d_state=128 (rev21's 256 freeze DEMOTED in rev24 as capacity-not-the-lever), target r_H (rev8), loss IC (rev10), timescales/d_conv defaults (rev14/16), L=216000, d_model=256. SWEEP: dropout in {0.1,0.3,0.5} x wd in {1e-3,1e-2}, 4 cells [(0.1,1e-3)=baseline, (0.3,1e-3), (0.5,1e-3), (0.3,1e-2)]. SUBSTRATE: LTC-only (train LTC < 2025-12-10, eval LTC >=); chosen over pooled because rev18 showed LTC-only +0.0158 > pooled all-8 +0.0110 AND it is ~8x cheaper; STRIDE=1 full days (the stride5/day-stride compute side-task showed -25% cap_edge from dropping 4/5 days, so stride would confound the reg signal -> keep full days for fidelity). SELECTION = RELATIVE cap_edge_gross (mean over H {180,600,1800} on LTC OOS) across the reg cells, vs the (0.1,1e-3) baseline ~+0.0158; NO 0.13% econ gate (rev19). epoch_hist now persisted -> can see if stronger reg shifts the val peak later/higher. METHOD: screen seed0 on train_big (H100-pref + A100 fallback), spawn + --detach, idempotent -> poll; if a reg cell beats baseline by > seed-sd, 3-seed confirm; else keep default (0.1,1e-3). This is the regularization lever of the rev24 pivot (effective-data-limited regime); the other lever (effective-sample de-correlation) is separate and does not cut compute. rev1-24 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-26T05:00:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HDX", "rev": 3, "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-26T04:10:00Z", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": "hdx-20260526_xgb_snapshot_Hsweep_1800", "note": "rev3: H-axis extended to 1800, IC objective FROZEN (user 2026-05-26; sq dropped). cap_edge_gross PEAKS at H600 (+0.0098, sd0.001), DROPS to ~0 at H1800 (+0.0014, sd0.004) -- corrects rev2's 'rises beyond 600'. med|move| keeps rising (0.057->0.200%): long-H moves larger but the last-tick snapshot loses directional skill on them. Contrast Mamba-2 (concentrates at H1800): temporal context shifts productive horizon outward. VM kept alive for next cell. Uncommitted append.", "statement": "HDX rev3 - H-AXIS EXTENDED to 1800 (IC objective FROZEN per user; objective-family NOT swept). Full cap_edge_gross(H) surface (IC, 46-feat decision-tick snapshot, pooled-8 train days<2025-12-10 / eval LTC n_ev=15812, window>=2024-12-25, 3 seeds, %/trade): H180 +0.0048+-0.0010, H300 +0.0056+-0.0011, H600 +0.0098+-0.0010 (ARGMAX, seed-stable), H1800 +0.0014+-0.0041 (collapses to ~0, noisy). PRIMARY READ: captured alpha PEAKS at H600 and DECLINES by H1800 for the snapshot -- NOT monotone-rising (corrects rev2's projection). med|move| rises monotonically (0.057->0.076->0.113->0.200%): long-H moves are LARGER but the last-tick snapshot loses DIRECTIONAL skill on them (cap_edge falls while magnitude rises). CONTRAST (cross-model, same labels/grid/eval): HD2 Mamba-2 (long-context L-stream) concentrates captured alpha at H1800; XGB-on-snapshot peaks at H600 -> the temporal L-CONTEXT shifts the productive horizon OUTWARD; snapshot 'sees' ~<=10min, the stream reaches ~30min. H-argmax for XGB-on-snapshot = 600s. SECONDARY (not headline, HD2 rev19): magnitudes ~0.005-0.010 %/trade below the 0.13% cost floor; cost not a criterion at the surface stage. NEXT (HDX_LEVERS A1/E2 = context/feature axis): give XGB MORE than the last tick (lagged K-tick snapshot window via hd1_seq_build --max-l K, or engineered rollups) and re-sweep H -> tests whether ADDED CONTEXT recovers H1800 captured alpha / shifts the argmax outward (i.e. whether the snapshot-vs-stream gap is CONTEXT, the data axis, vs the Mamba architecture). VM hdx-rust kept alive (no poweroff) for this. rev1-2 UNCHANGED."}
{"hypothesis_id": "HD2", "note": "rev26 reg re-pass RESULT (rev25 confirm): the seed0 screen winner dropout=0.3 (0.0167) did NOT survive 3 seeds. 3-seed cap_edge_gross (LTC-only stride1, %/trade): d0.1 = 0.0098 +-0.0011 (s0 .0089,s1 .0092,s2 .0114); d0.3 = 0.0107 +-0.0050 (s0 .0167,s1 .0111,s2 .0044); d0.4 s0 = 0.0145. d0.3 lead over d0.1 = 0.0009 << seed-sd (d0.3 sd alone 0.0050) -> NOT separable; the val-peak-delay mechanism (ep2->ep4) was also seed-specific (d0.3 bestEp [4,0,0]). DECISION: keep dropout=0.1 (default) -- also more seed-stable (sd 0.0011 vs 0.0050; more dropout -> more stochasticity -> noisier). reg lever (the rev24 pivot's reg arm) does NOT robustly move cap_edge at scale, consistent with rev12 (flat reg on 500d). META: cap_edge on LTC-only is highly seed-unstable (sd up to ~50% of mean), so single-seed screens here are unreliable -> the seed0-only capacity screens (d_state rev21, n_layers rev22) are retroactively within-noise too (their 'peaks' ds256=0.0146 / nl4 likely seed draws). UNIFYING SURFACE: across ALL architecture/reg/capacity axes cap_edge ~0.01-0.015% +- large seed noise; the only condition that robustly MAXIMIZED captured alpha was the OBJECTIVE (IC vs R1, rev10, 3-seed +0.0230+-0.0003 >> R1 +0.0082+-0.0079). Ceiling set by signal content in data/features, not model tuning. rev1-25 UNCHANGED.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 26, "statement": "HD2 rev26 - regularization re-pass RESULT + seed-stability meta (exploratory surface, CLAUDE.md). SURFACE (RELATIVE cap_edge_gross, LTC-only stride1, %/trade, 3 seeds): dropout 0.1 = 0.0098 +-0.0011; dropout 0.3 = 0.0107 +-0.0050; dropout 0.4 (seed0 only) = 0.0145. The dropout=0.3 lead seen in the seed0 screen (0.0167 vs 0.0089) DISSOLVED under 3 seeds: d0.3 collapses to 0.0107 with seed-sd 0.0050 (range 0.0044-0.0167), overlapping d0.1's 0.0098+-0.0011; the gap (0.0009) is far below the seed noise. ARGMAX by 3-seed mean is nominally d0.3 but it is not separable from default and is markedly LESS seed-stable. DECISION: freeze dropout at the default 0.1 (equal alpha within noise, ~5x lower seed-sd). The regularization lever does not robustly raise captured alpha at scale (consistent with rev12's flat reg on 500d). METHODOLOGICAL FINDING: captured-alpha on the LTC-only substrate has large seed variance (sd up to ~50% of the mean), so single-seed screens are unreliable here; this retroactively places the seed0-only capacity screens (d_state rev21, n_layers rev22) within noise as well. UNIFYING CHARACTERIZATION of the Mamba-2 conditional surface: across objective, loss, reg, timescales, d_conv, and capacity (d_state/n_layers), the ONLY axis that robustly and seed-stably MAXIMIZED cap_edge was the OBJECTIVE choice (IC, rev10: +0.0230+-0.0003 vs R1 +0.0082+-0.0079, 3-seed); every architecture/regularization/capacity knob sits within seed noise (~0.01-0.015% on LTC-only). The captured-alpha ceiling is therefore set by the signal content of the data/features, not by model hyperparameters. NO 0.13% econ gate (rev19). rev1-25 UNCHANGED (append-only). STATUS testing.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-26T05:50:00Z"}
{"hypothesis_id": "HDX", "rev": 4, "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-26T05:10:00Z", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": "hdx-20260526_xgb_context_Ksweep", "note": "rev4: context-length K-sweep (XGB analog of HD2 L-sweep). MORE context DEGRADES XGB (K=1 snapshot dominates; cap_edge falls with K; H1800 ~0 for all K). => snapshot-vs-Mamba gap is ARCHITECTURE (sequential integration), not data/context: XGB on the same K-tick window does worse (flattened lags + dimensionality). Strongest XGB condition = snapshot K=1 @ H600. VM destroyed post-sweep per user; flaky SSH triple-launched (convergent json). Uncommitted append.", "statement": "HDX rev4 - CONTEXT-LENGTH axis (XGB analog of HD2 L-sweep), IC objective. Q (from rev3): does flattening a K-tick window of the 46 tick-features into XGBoost recover long-H captured alpha / shift the H-argmax outward toward Mamba-2's H1800? K in {1,8,32} x H {180,600,1800}, cap_edge_gross %/trade (eval LTC n=15812, 3 seeds). SURFACE: K=1 (snapshot,46f) H180 +0.0048+-0.0010 / H600 +0.0098+-0.0010 (GLOBAL ARGMAX) / H1800 +0.0014+-0.0041; K=8 (368f) +0.0044/+0.0045/+0.0002; K=32 (1472f) +0.0004/+0.0023/+0.0026. PRIMARY READ: MORE context DEGRADES, not helps -- K=1 dominates at EVERY H; cap_edge falls ~monotonically with K (esp at the productive H600: 0.0098->0.0045->0.0023); H1800 stays ~0 for all K (context did NOT shift the productive horizon outward). ANSWER to rev3: the snapshot-vs-Mamba gap is the ARCHITECTURE (sequential temporal integration), NOT merely data/context -- XGB given the SAME K-tick context does WORSE (trees cannot model the temporal structure of flattened lags; curse of dimensionality 46->1472 feats dilutes the signal). For XGBoost the STRONGEST condition = SNAPSHOT (K=1) at H=600s (+0.0098, seed-stable); the long-H regime belongs to the sequence model. SECONDARY (HD2 rev19): magnitudes <0.13% cost floor, not the criterion at surface stage. INFRA NOTE: flaky Windows->gcloud SSH triple-launched the orchestrator (3 procs, convergent json); cleaned via VM teardown (per user: destroy post-sweep). NEXT axes (HDX_LEVERS A/E): feature-SUBSTRATE (vs the 46 tick-feats), selectivity, pooling/scope -- on the NEXT account post-migration. rev1-3 UNCHANGED."}
