{"hypothesis_id": "HM7", "rev": 1, "ts": "2026-05-17T22:10:00Z", "statement": "FEATURE INVENTORY & ANTI-REDUNDANCY CANON (user 2026-05-17: next agent re-proposes liquidations / ETH-following without knowing they are already in the XGB feature set / or are present-but-DEAD). MANDATORY READ before proposing any feature/data hypothesis. The exact XGB model input for baseline_ref (HM6) and EVERY screen (HA1/HA5/HR1/HA2/H3/baseline_360) = features_v1 (decoded cols 0-55 + CRYPTOLAKE_EXT 56-58; full map in research/CRYPTOLAKE_SCHEMA.md) PLUS per-run live _cond_feats COND_KEYS = {liq_sq_30s,liq_n_30s,liq_sq_120s,liq_n_120s} (signed liquidation qty+counts 30/120s causal, from raw/liquidations; src scripts/ha5_screen.py). Source of truth: src/features.py::FEATURE_KEYS, rust_ingest/src/features.rs, ha5_screen._cond_feats/COND_KEYS, CRYPTOLAKE_SCHEMA.md decoded+DEAD section. ALREADY-COVERED (do NOT re-propose as novel; cite this): (1) LIQUIDATIONS — present & LIVE: features_v1 col19 liquidation_proximity is DEAD/constant(=0.015) BUT EXT cols 56-58 (liq/OI magnitude) are live AND liq_sq/liq_n 30/120s appended live every run incl. HM6 baseline_ref; dedicated test HA5 REFUTED (its note: hand-built liq/OI/funding conditioners 'largely DUPLICATED already-live features_v1 cols'). Only a materially different construction (e.g. cascade-timing, cross-symbol liq contagion) is new. (2) ETH-FOLLOWING / cross-asset — TWO-SIDED: features_v1 ETH cols {14 eth_momentum_1s,15 eth_ofi,16 eth_leading_signal,54 eth_momentum_60s,55 eth_btc_corr_30s} EXIST but are 100% DEAD(zero) in all builds -> via features_v1 NOT a valid test; HOWEVER live cross-asset WAS properly tested: H3 (BTC-lead, btc_cols_live=1.0 -> WEAK symbol-inconsistent marginal, 4/8 cells neg, stacking-only) and HA2 +xasset (8 live BTC-lead+8 live ETH-lead two-head -> REFUTED as posed; SOL-only faint sub-cost whisper d+0.009..0.016, LINK ~0). So ETH/BTC-lead is tested-and-weak, NOT untested; re-proposing naive 'use eth_ cols' is invalid (dead) AND re-proposing 'follow ETH/BTC' duplicates H3/HA2. (3) OI/funding (cols 13,17,44,56-57) — in HA5 (refuted). KEY HONESTY RULE: 'present in features_v1' != 'tested' when the col is in the DEAD list; conversely cross-asset/liq ARE tested via H3/HA2/HA5. A new feature/data hypothesis is admissible ONLY if it is materially different from these and states why, vs this inventory.", "status": "confirmed", "priority_rank": 0, "result_experiment_id": null, "note": "Intercepts the next agent's redundant proposals at the ledger (where hypotheses are proposed). Honest both ways: stops re-proposing already-live/already-refuted signals AND stops mistaking DEAD features_v1 cols for prior tests. Pointers to all source-of-truth files; defers to CRYPTOLAKE_SCHEMA.md for the full decoded map."}
{"hypothesis_id": "HDATA", "note": "Created per user 2026-05-23 as ONE broad, deliberately unbounded training-data axis -- no hardcoded limiters. Dimensions/levels are filled empirically by each run's own pre-registration; this entry imposes none. Provenance is the only constraint.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 1, "statement": "OPEN data-axis container (exploratory conditional-optimization, HD1-style; deliberately UNBOUNDED). QUESTION: under what training-data composition do models best extract directional signal? DELIVERABLE = an accumulating conditional rank_IC surface over training-data-composition variables, filled cell-by-cell over time. NO dimension or level is pre-enumerated or bounded by THIS entry: any aspect of the training data -- what data, from where, over what span and prediction horizon, in what single-/multi-/cross-asset structure, read by any probe model -- is in scope; what varies and at what levels is declared by each run's own frozen pre-registration, never constrained here. Rigor lives ONLY in per-result provenance (data_source, n_eff, split_method, cost basis, repro_cmd) so the surface stays trustworthy and reusable -- not in restricting axes. SELECTION during search = robust marginal delta_ic vs a declared baseline_ref (standing SELECTION POLICY); the section-5 economic gate is a DEMOTED secondary annotation, never the headline or a per-cell kill. Subsumes the scattered open data notes (HD1 multi-symbol/horizon pooling 'real n_eff multiplier', data-scale) into one container instead of fragmenting into correlated narrow overlapping hypotheses.", "status": "active", "ts": "2026-05-22T23:08:46Z"}
{"compute_cost_usd": "Phase0 $0 (existing rev28 GCS artifacts). Phases1-4: USDC data pull from data.binance.vision (egress + GCS storage; aggTrades is the heavy leg) + 1 GCP 96vCPU run -> est. low-tens-$. Scope + sign-off REQUIRED before pull.", "compute_time": "Phase0 ~minutes (eval-only re-sim). Phases1-4: pull ~hours (bandwidth-bound) + ~1-2h GCP.", "expected_lift": "Phase0 prize (gross, before USDC fill haircut): zeroing the maker-fee term lifts the rev28 deployable-maker surface from -4..-5 bp/trade toward ~0..+3 bp/trade (the maker round-trip term is the dominant cost). Net deploy value = that lift MINUS the USDC spread/adverse-selection haircut (Phase 4, unknown until measured).", "hypothesis_id": "HUSDC", "note": "rev1 = frozen pre-registration of the USDC<->USDT transfer method, on branch claude/husdc-rev1. PRE-RUN: nothing built. VERIFIED 2026-05-28: (a) USDC-margined PERPETUALs exist on Binance fapi; (b) their history IS on data.binance.vision (futures/um/daily/aggTrades/BTCUSDC/ present, dumps back to >=2024-01) at top-of-book + trade granularity (NO full L2 depth in daily dumps); (c) maker fee = 0.0000% for ALL USDC-margined perps, all VIP tiers, 'until further notice' (prev extended past 2026-04-01), taker ~0.04% VIP0. The 'we only have USDT data' difficulty is the 585GB bucket being USDT-only with full L2; USDC is acquirable but only at top-of-book+trade granularity historically -> the design is a fit-on-USDT / score-on-USDC TRANSFER test on the common observable + a fee-schedule swap, NOT a from-scratch USDC fit. Phase0 is free and runs on existing data; Phases1-4 are behind a data-pull cost gate. Per README selection policy: keep/kill by robust marginal delta vs the USDT-self baseline, the maker break-even read is a demoted deploy annotation. Committed on branch, NOT pushed (CLAUDE.md: no push without explicit permission).", "prerequisites": "Phase0: rev28 deployable grid_sim artifacts on gs://market-data-0998ac51. Phases1-4: USDC perp data pull (data.binance.vision + Binance fapi WS for forward full-depth) -- COST GATE, user sign-off required per CLAUDE.md before the pull. Nothing built/run at rev1.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 1, "statement": "HUSDC rev1 - USDC-PERP <-> USDT-PERP SIGNAL TRANSFER + 0%-MAKER ECONOMIC SWAP (pre-registered, frozen PRE-RUN; Phase 0 free, Phases 1-4 awaiting USDC-data-pull cost sign-off). HYPOTHESIS: USDC-margined perp microstructure correlates with the USDT-margined perp strongly enough that a signal FIT on USDT (the HD2 sub-60s vol-head + dir-head) retains predictive skill and economic decile structure when SCORED on USDC; and because Binance charges 0.0000% maker on ALL USDC-margined perps (verified 2026-05-28, 'until further notice', taker ~0.04% VIP0), a USDT-derived signal that is sub-cost-at-maker on USDT (HD2 rev28 deployable-maker -4..-5 bp/trade, the maker-fee term being the dominant cost) can become NET-POSITIVE when deployed MAKER-ONLY on USDC. WHY THIS IS PIVOTAL: the entire rev28 deployable surface is sub-cost ONLY because of the maker fee; a 0% maker fee is the difference between 'trade at a loss' and 'large plus' - it is the economic gate the whole program runs into. THE DIFFICULTY + ITS RESOLUTION: our 585 GB bucket (gs://market-data-0998ac51) is USDT-only with full L2 LOB; USDC is NOT in the bucket. BUT USDC-perp history IS publicly acquirable from data.binance.vision (futures/um/daily/{aggTrades,bookTicker,klines,metrics}/<SYM>USDC/, verified present) at TOP-OF-BOOK + trade granularity (NOT full L2 depth), and live full-depth via Binance fapi WS for forward recording. So the test is NOT a from-scratch USDC fit (we lack USDC L2 history) but a TRANSFER TEST on the COMMON OBSERVABLE (aggTrades taker-flow/CVD, bookTicker top-of-book spread + L1 imbalance, returns, trailing realized vol, |rH60| labels) plus a fee-schedule swap. METHOD (nested, cheap-first, each phase gates the next): PHASE 0 (FREE, zero new data): re-run the EXISTING rev28 deployable grid_sim on USDT features with the USDC fee schedule (maker 0.0000%, taker 0.0400%) instead of standard USDT maker -> quantifies the PRIZE (how far the -4..-5 bp/trade deployable-maker surface moves toward/over break-even when the maker term is zeroed), per symbol, at matched trades/day; runs on data already paid for. PHASE 1 - RETURN CO-MOVEMENT (Q1, necessary floor): pull USDC counterparts for the bucket symbols that HAVE a USDC perp, same window (2025-05-09..2026-05-08); corr of 1s/15s/60s log-returns USDC vs USDT (mid from bookTicker, trade price from aggTrades). Expect ~0.99; drop any symbol whose USDC return-corr is low (too thin to mirror). PHASE 2 - MICROSTRUCTURE / SIGNAL-INPUT CO-MOVEMENT (Q2): contemporaneous + lead-lag (+/- N x 100ms) corr of the ACTUAL MODEL INPUTS between USDC and USDT - top-of-book spread (bp), L1 imbalance, taker-flow imbalance/CVD, trailing realized vol {1,5,15,30 min}, |rH60| label distribution; the lead-lag profile bounds how far USDT (the volume leader) LEADS USDC = the latency cost of sourcing the signal on USDT and executing on USDC. PHASE 3 - SIGNAL TRANSFER (Q3, the real test): SCORE the HD2-USDT-fit vol/dir heads on USDC features WITHOUT refitting (common-observable columns only; any full-L2-dependent column ABLATED on BOTH sides for an apples-to-apples compare); measure on USDC honest-OOS rank-IC of the vol-head |move| ranking, dir-head accuracy on the conviction tail, decile monotonicity, top-decile |move|; 'signal transfers' iff the USDC metrics sit within a stated band of the SAME ablated model scored on USDT (degradation, not collapse to noise). Selection by ROBUST marginal delta vs the USDT-self baseline (baseline_ref), NOT by an economic gate (README selection policy). PHASE 4 - ECONOMIC PUNCHLINE (Q4, decisive): re-run the deployable grid_sim on USDC features with (a) USDC fees (maker 0%) AND (b) USDC FILL REALISM - spread (bp) + top-of-book depth measured from USDC bookTicker fed into the SAME 150ms-latency / 1s-fill-window adverse-selection model used on USDT. The 0% prize is real ONLY if maker fills are achievable on the thinner USDC book; the USDC spread/adverse-selection haircut PARTIALLY OFFSETS the fee saving -> quantify the NET deployable-maker EV/trade (USDC@0% vs USDT@standard) at matched trades/day. PRIMARY DELIVERABLE (continuous, per CLAUDE.md): the transfer-degradation surface (Q3) CROSSED with the fee-vs-fill economic surface (Q0 + Q4), per symbol - 'how much predictive skill survives the transfer' x 'how much of the 0%-maker prize survives USDC fill realism'. SECONDARY (demoted deploy annotation, NOT a selector): does any symbol clear maker break-even on USDC. LIMITS / HONESTY: (i) daily dumps give top-of-book + trades, NOT full L2 -> full-depth USDC features only via a forward WS recorder track (staged separately); Phases 2-4 are bounded to the common observable. (ii) USDC volume << USDT -> FILL REALISM (Phase 4) is the BINDING risk, not price corr (Phase 1, which is near-trivially ~0.99). (iii) The 0% maker fee is a PROMOTION ('until further notice'), a policy variable not a guarantee - the deploy value is contingent on it persisting. COST GATE: Phase 0 free (existing data); Phases 1-4 require a USDC data pull (egress + GCS storage) + a GCP run - scope + user sign-off REQUIRED before the pull, per CLAUDE.md. rev1 is the spec ONLY; nothing built/run. DATA CONTRACT: source = data.binance.vision futures/um/daily/{aggTrades,bookTicker,klines,metrics}/<SYM>USDC + Binance fapi WS (forward full-depth); land in gs://market-data-0998ac51 under raw/.../symbol=<SYM>USDC mirroring the USDT layout; fees USDC = maker 0.0000% / taker 0.0400% (VIP0), USDT comparison = standard.", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-28T12:00:00Z"}
{"compute_cost_usd": "CHEAP. STEP A/B: pull USDC top-of-book (bookTicker) + trades (aggTrades) for ~8 syms x ~1y from data.binance.vision (egress + GCS storage; aggTrades is the heavy leg, NO L2). STEP C reuses it + existing rev28 USDT predictions. ~1 GCP run. Scope + sign-off required before pull. Full-L2 / forward-recording / vendor purchase EXPLICITLY OUT (budget).", "compute_time": "pull ~hours (bandwidth-bound) + ~1-2h GCP. No multi-week recording window (that path is closed).", "expected_lift": "Net deployable-maker EV/trade on USDC = (rev28 USDT gross capture that survives the USDT->USDC signal mirror) + (full maker-fee saving, since USDC maker = 0%) - (USDC spread/adverse-selection haircut on the thin book). Sign/magnitude unknown until STEP C; the 0% fee removes the dominant cost term that keeps the USDT surface at -4..-5 bp/trade.", "hypothesis_id": "HUSDC", "note": "rev2 = PIVOT (owner decision 2026-05-28): model-transfer-to-USDC is CLOSED -- we cannot afford full-fidelity USDC features (historical dumps are top-of-book + trades only, NO full L2; a year of forward L2 recording or a vendor L2 purchase is out of budget). New design = SIGNAL-MIRROR: compute the signal on USDT (full data + rev28 model, as today) and EXECUTE maker-only on the USDC perp to capture the 0.0000% maker fee. Needs ONLY USDC top-of-book + trades (cheap, historical) -> dissolves the data problem. SELF-CORRECTION of rev1: rev1 demoted lead-lag as 'only-for-signal-mirroring' and droppable; under this pivot it is CENTRAL (the bridge that makes a USDT signal valid for a USDC order). rev1 Phase0 (USDT fee-swap proxy) and Phase1 (return corr) dropped as redundant/trivial; rev1 Phase3 (score 64-col model on USDC features) CLOSED. Branch claude/husdc-rev1, committed, NOT pushed. rev1 UNCHANGED (append-only).", "prerequisites": "Existing rev28 USDT vol/dir predictions (timestamp + direction/conviction) as artifacts. USDC top-of-book + trades pull (data.binance.vision) -- COST GATE, user sign-off per CLAUDE.md before pulling. Nothing built/run at rev2.", "priority_rank": 1, "result_experiment_id": null, "rev": 2, "statement": "HUSDC rev2 - PIVOT to SIGNAL-MIRROR (USDT-computed signal executed maker-only on 0%-fee USDC); model-transfer-to-USDC CLOSED. DECISION (owner, 2026-05-28): full-fidelity USDC features are unaffordable - historical data.binance.vision dumps are top-of-book (bookTicker) + trades (aggTrades) only, NO full L2, and a year of forward L2 recording or a vendor L2 purchase is out of budget - so rev1's Phase 3 ('score the 64-col rev28 model on USDC features') is CLOSED. NEW ARCHITECTURE: keep the signal where the data lives (compute the rev28 sub-60s vol/dir signal on USDT, full features, exactly as today) and EXECUTE maker-only orders on the USDC perp to capture the 0.0000% USDC maker fee. This exploits the asymmetry directly: USDT = data-rich + price-leader, USDC = fee-free execution venue. SELF-CORRECTION of rev1: lead-lag/basis (rev1 'Phase 2', which rev1 demoted as only-for-signal-mirroring and droppable) is now CENTRAL - it is the bridge that makes a USDT signal valid for a USDC order. CRUCIAL DATA CONSEQUENCE: this design needs ONLY USDC top-of-book + trades, which ARE available historically and cheaply -> no full L2, no forward-recording window, no vendor purchase. METHOD (signal-mirror, cheap, historical, cheap-first): STEP A - TRACKING + LEAD-LAG + BASIS: from USDC bookTicker/aggTrades vs USDT, measure (1) contemporaneous mid-corr; (2) the USDT->USDC lead-lag cross-correlation - does USDC LAG USDT and by how many ms (a lag is GOOD: the USDT signal then predicts USDC's near-future move); (3) the basis (USDC_mid - USDT_mid) level/vol/mean-reversion + decoupling episodes (BASIS RISK: a USDT signal firing while USDC is temporarily decoupled = bad fills / wrong side). Latency context: HH rev1 found OBI edge half-life secs..tens-of-secs, budget ~<=1-2 s, so sub-second lead-lag is tolerable - confirm. STEP B - SIGNAL VALIDITY ON USDC (the reframed transfer test): take the EXISTING rev28 USDT predictions (timestamp + predicted direction/conviction; NO refit), align to the USDC clock, and score them against USDC's REALIZED forward move (label computed from USDC bookTicker mid / aggTrades). The features stay USDT; ONLY the LABEL switches to USDC. 'Signal carries' iff the USDT-prediction rank-IC / dir-acc-on-conviction-tail against USDC labels sits within a stated band of the SAME predictions scored against USDT labels. Selection by robust marginal delta vs the USDT-self baseline (README policy), NOT an economic gate. STEP C - ECONOMIC: USDC MAKER FILLS @ 0% FEE (was Phase 4, decisive): deployable grid_sim with entries/exits simulated ON THE USDC BOOK (spread + top-of-book depth from USDC bookTicker), maker fee 0.0000%, taker 0.0400%, the SAME 150ms-latency / 1s-fill-window adverse-selection model used on USDT, gated by the USDT-signal timing from STEP B. Quantify NET deployable-maker EV/trade on USDC at matched trades/day vs USDT@standard-maker. The 0% prize is real ONLY if maker fills clear adverse selection on the thin USDC book. PRIMARY DELIVERABLE (continuous, per CLAUDE.md): USDC-signal-validity (STEP B rank-IC vs USDT-self baseline) CROSSED with USDC-execution-economics (STEP C EV/trade surface), per symbol. SECONDARY (demoted deploy annotation, NOT a selector): does any symbol clear break-even on USDC at 0% maker. LIMITS / HONESTY: (i) the USDC fill model is TOP-OF-BOOK fidelity (no full L2 historically) -> the adverse-selection / queue sim is first-order; a forward full-depth recorder would refine STEP C but is EXPLICITLY OUT of scope (budget). (ii) BASIS RISK: USDT and USDC perps can decouple (funding / liquidity / stress) - STEP A quantifies it; a decoupled-state filter may be required before STEP C. (iii) CAPACITY: USDC volume << USDT - even at positive EV/trade, size is bounded; STEP C reports achievable trades/day + top-of-book depth as the capacity read. (iv) the 0% maker fee is a PROMOTION ('until further notice'), policy not guarantee. COST GATE: STEP A/B are CHEAP (USDC top-of-book + trades pull, NO L2) - scope the pull (~8 syms x ~1 y aggTrades + bookTicker) + user sign-off per CLAUDE.md before pulling; STEP C reuses the same data + existing rev28 predictions. rev2 is the spec ONLY; nothing built/run. DATA CONTRACT: source = data.binance.vision futures/um/daily/{aggTrades,bookTicker}/<SYM>USDC (+ klines/metrics if needed); land in gs://market-data-0998ac51 under raw/.../symbol=<SYM>USDC; the USDT signal = existing rev28 prediction artifacts; fees USDC = maker 0.0000% / taker 0.0400% (VIP0), USDT comparison = standard. rev1 Phase0/Phase1 dropped, Phase3-model-transfer CLOSED; rev1 row UNCHANGED (append-only).", "status": "testing", "ts": "2026-05-28T13:30:00Z"}
