NAL-MIRROR (compute signal on USDT, execute maker-only on 0%-fee USDC). run1 (exp 2026-05-28T1247Z_husdc_run1_coupling) ran the cheap aggTrades-only mechanism screen on DOGE/SOL/ETH/BTC x 14d (2026-05-01..05-14), n2-standard-4 europe-west1, self-stopped. CONTINUOUS SURFACE (per CLAUDE.md - report the surface, not a verdict): STEP A COUPLING (the necessary condition) IS STRONG AND UNIFORM - contemporaneous corr(USDC,USDT) rises 0.85-0.96 @5s -> 0.987-0.995 @60s, beta 0.78-0.98 (USDC slightly under-moves on thin DOGE/SOL @5s), basis log(USDC/USDT) mean -0.14..-1.12 bp / sd 1.0-1.8 bp / AR1 0.78-0.97 (stationary, mean-reverting), and DECOUPLING fraction beyond 5 sd = 0.0000 for ALL 4 symbols -> USDC is a tight, stable, non-decoupling mirror of USDT at the 30-60s horizons the strategy trades; lead-lag is at the noise floor (|corr|<0.034, near-synchronous, no exploitable or penalizing lead). STEP C FIRST-ORDER ECONOMICS - Roll effective-spread (trades-only, crude) USDC 0.00-0.21 bp vs USDT 0.31-1.70 bp (USDC is NOT wider), so the verified USDC 0.0000% maker removes the ~11 bp USDT maker round-trip and DWARFS any spread difference by an order of magnitude: the fee swap is the lever that moves rev28 deployable-maker (-4..-5 bp/trade) toward/over break-even - CONDITIONAL on transfer + achievable maker fills. STEP B TRANSFER IS INCONCLUSIVE BECAUSE OF A LABEL ARTIFACT (recorded honestly, not as a verdict): the USDC forward-return label built from asof-last-trade mid is contaminated by non-synchronous-trading catch-up - on the sparser DOGE/SOL the SAME USDT predictor shows IC_USDT<0 but IC_USDC>0 (a sign flip = the stale USDC mid catching up to USDT's just-completed move, NOT genuine predictability), making the transfer ratio uninterpretable there; on dense BTC/ETH (USDC trade-gap ~0 s) IC_USDT and IC_USDC share sign with transfer ~0.12-0.41 @15s, an attenuated-but-positive first read. The recorded rank_ic_oos=0.027 is the dense-symbol USDC-fwd IC of trail_ret_5s@15s, a weak 