al, skill axis) after removing the run1 label artifact. CONTEXT: run1 (rev3) found tight coupling + a big fee prize but its Step B transfer was contaminated by non-synchronous-trading (the asof-last-trade USDC forward label was stale -> catch-up bias, flipping IC signs on sparse DOGE/SOL). run2 (exp 2026-05-28T1516Z_husdc_run2_freshlabel) rebuilt the label with MATCHED FRESHNESS: a grid point counts toward a forward rank-IC only if BOTH contracts traded within 1s of BOTH t and t+H, so neither mid is stale (validated offline: in a synthetic stale-USDC case the inflated raw USDC IC collapses toward the USDT IC). CONTINUOUS SURFACE (per CLAUDE.md): (1) ARTIFACT REMOVED - under the fresh label every IC sign is consistent (USDT and USDC same-sign positive) and the raw nonsense transfer ratios (-14.89, +60..) become sane. (2) TRANSFER (the sufficient-condition-on-skill) IS CONFIRMED DIRECTIONALLY - fresh IC_USDC is POSITIVE for all 4 symbols x {trail_ret_5s, trail_ret_30s, tfi_30s} x {15s,60s}, with magnitude comparable to the USDT-self IC (fresh IC ~0.025-0.06); transfer coefficient IC_USDC/IC_USDT = DOGE ~1.0-1.7, SOL ~1.0-2.0, ETH ~0.49-0.86, BTC ~0.54-1.07. The signal's predictive DIRECTION carries from USDT to USDC forward moves with NO sign collapse; on thinner USDC (DOGE/SOL) transfer is ~full-or-stronger, on dense BTC/ETH it is attenuated-but-clearly-positive (~0.5-0.9, USDC's own microstructure noise the likely attenuator). (3) COUPLING is even tighter under freshness (fresh contemporaneous corr 0.97-0.997 @60s; beta 0.78-0.98; basis sd ~1-1.8bp, AR1 0.78-0.97, DECOUPLE=0.0000) and lead-lag is small/near-synchronous with a slight USDT lead at 60s on SOL/BTC (consistent with USDT being the price leader). (4) ECONOMICS unchanged: USDC Roll spread <= USDT, the 0% USDC maker reclaims ~11-12bp round-trip >> any spread difference. Fresh coverage = 33-51% of seconds = exactly the moments with a two-sided fresh market when a maker strategy can act. VERDICT (continuous, n